editorialSummary: Popular sports bar in a low-key, rustic space serving elevated pub fare & local draft beer.
reviewSummary:
People say this sports bar offers a great selection of beers, delicious wings, and tasty chili. They also highlight the friendly and attentive service, as well as the lively atmosphere.

Some reviews mention the food can be overpriced.
reviews:
[{"rating": 5, "text": "Let‚Äôs talk ambiance‚Äîthis place is massive and totally sets the vibe! Whether you're planning a girls' brunch, a cute date, or catching the game, it fits the mood. Oh, and if you love outdoor seating, they've got that covered too.

October Bonus: their spooky decor adds the perfect seasonal touch!

Now, onto the drinks‚Äîhad to try the Tap House's fresh-squeezed Crush, and wow, the difference between this and those syrupy cocktails? Instantly noticeable. So fresh, so good!

When it comes to brunch, I'm still thinking about that pancake board‚Äîsuch a great portion for the price. We also went for their $45 bottomless brunch (90 minutes!) which includes one entr√©e.

One word for the marshmallow s'mores chocolate French toast: magical. It gave total cozy, Christmassy vibes.

For something savory, we had the Benedicts‚Äîand they did not disappoint. I had the best time here, and I seriously think you‚Äôll love it too. Highly recommend checking it out!", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a week ago", "authorName": "Vinita Badani"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "Really awesome place for brunch! The vibe was super chill, the service was friendly, and the food was really quite excellent. We sat outside as it was a gorgeous day by the shore. I went with family and ordered the boozy bunch with mimosas, a breakfast board which was huge, the scrambler (my favorite), and eggs benedict. Food came out quickly and the potions were huge. I took half my scrambler back home. There was also some games like a giant connect four and cornhole by the sofas in the back of the patio area. Definitely a great value for what you get and it was not too crowded for a holiday weekend. If I am around the Spring Lake area again, I would definitely return, maybe next time for dinner or happy hour (they had a board that listed some excellent happy hour deals).", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a month ago", "authorName": "Mark Birch"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "If you‚Äôre looking for the ultimate Jersey Shore brunch spot, Spring Lake Taphouse is one you‚Äôll definitely want on your list.

Would you believe you can get 90 minutes of unlimited brunch cocktails and a full entr√©e for just $45/person? Yup!! Go with the Boozy Brunch where you can get unlimited brunch cocktails (pick one drink) and an entree per person (everyone at your table must participate). We went with classic mimosas for our drinks. Very nice to sip on as we hung out on their spacious back patio. For entr√©es, we tried the build your own omelette ‚Äî light and fluffy ‚Äî and their breakfast pizza, which hits that perfect balance of cheesy, savory brunch vibes and lots of meat (pork roll, sausage and bacon). The crust was nice and crispy!

Then came the showstopper ‚Äî the pancake board!! A dozen mini pancakes with bacon, scrambled eggs, and fresh fruit ‚Äî basically brunch heaven on one platter. This serves about 2-3 people and awesome to share.

And for the most relatable dish on the menu? The ‚ÄòMy GF Isn‚Äôt Hungry‚Äô board ‚Äî every kind of fry you can think of, with delicious house-made dipping sauces. Another awesome board for sharing which you can pick on all brunch long.

We sat out back on their patio ‚Äî tons of seating, couches, cornhole, and yes, you can even bring your dog. It‚Äôs laid-back, fun, and perfect for a weekend hangout. The service is very friendly and attentive and we had a great time! I would definitely return for brunch again.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "2 months ago", "authorName": "Lindsey Alexandria"}, {"rating": 4, "text": "A friend of mine and I got together for lunch. sea shore lettuce wrap

generativeSummary: Casual restaurant turning out familiar dishes such as jerk chicken and curry goat.
reviewSummary: People say this Jamaican restaurant serves delicious jerk chicken pasta, curry goat, oxtail, and beef patties. They highlight the generous portions and flavorful dishes. They also like the friendly staff and welcoming atmosphere.
reviews:
[{"rating": 5, "text": "There comes a time in every foreigners‚Äòs life when they yearn for home. I was born and raised in Jamaica and whenever I yearn for home, I go straight to Flavaz Jamaican Grille.

It‚Äôs not only about the delicious food. It‚Äôs about the Customer Service, the professional and fun interactions with staff, the vibes, the music and community.

I grew up cooking authentic Jamaican food with my mom and aunties and I later embodied that tradition with my own children and grandchildren , so I‚Äôm very particular about where and what I eat.

Flavaz gets 5 stars from me because i‚Äôm always satisfied when I go there to eat.

No matter the day of the week or what your palate desires, whether it‚Äôs curry goat, Ackee and saltfish with ground provisions, brown stew chicken, jerk chicken, curry chicken, shrimp, patties, coco bread, oxtails, soup, home juices or snacks  you will never ever be disappointed.

The price is reasonable, serving sizes are more than enough. The flavors and aroma keeps your mouth watering, your pallet happy and your tummy full.

The location, cleanliness of the establishment, and  the professionalism of their staff adds an extra layer of excellence.

Every time I visit Flavaz, I feel like I‚Äôm eating at home in Jamaica.

I am so grateful the Shaws bought the taste of Jamaica right here to Riverview.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "2 weeks ago", "authorName": "Megan Wedderburn"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "I tried jerk chicken for the first time when I was 14, and ever since then I‚Äôve never found a Jamaican restaurant as good as the one I had back in Jacksonville, FL‚Ä¶ until today.

I walked into Flavaz, ordered jerk chicken, and when she opened the box to show me the food real quick, I knew I had to try it right away. I wasn‚Äôt ready for how good this was about to be! I had stuff to do, but NOTHING else mattered once I took that first bite.

The sauce‚Ä¶oh my god‚Ä¶ the sauce was unreal. The rice and peas, cabbage, plantains‚Ä¶ everything was straight fire üî• I sat in my car and ate the whole thing without stopping.

I can‚Äôt wait to tell my friends and family about this spot. Flavaz just blew Jacksonville out of the water!", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a week ago", "authorName": "Lucas"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "Such an amazing place, the whole restaurant is very clean ( even restrooms ) and everyone is very humble and respectful. The food did not disappoint it was very great amazing taste, for someone who has never had Jamaican cuisine before i would definitely recommend it. May God bless this establishment üëèüèΩü§ç", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "2 months ago", "authorName": "oneissy rosado"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "Let me start by saying Delani customer service was very welcoming! [{"rating": 3, "text": "We were excited to check out this restaurant because of its good reviews and beautiful ambiance. Unfortunately, we were not very impressed with its food.
The service was good and fast.
My husband ordered the Chicken Parmesan. The chicken wasn‚Äôt crispy, it didn‚Äôt have enough flavor, and it was kind of soggy. It didn't taste good. The Pizza we got was flimsy and nothing special. The garlic knots were tasty but very small.
Campanella seems overpriced for the quality of food they offer.
Yes, both indoor and outdoor dining areas looked great, with beautiful pictures on the walls and nicely decorated tables, but unfortunately, that's not enough.
I don't think we will be back.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a week ago", "authorName": "Karolina H."}, {"rating": 5, "text": "This cute Italian restaurant totally surprised us ‚Äî in the best way. We shared two pasta dishes ‚Äî a tomato-based one and a basil pesto ‚Äî and both were so good. Simple, flavorful, and clearly made with care. One was gluten free and it was great! The service was just as impressive: warm, attentive, and perfectly paced.

If you‚Äôre looking for something easy, delicious, and not overly fussy, this is a great pick. A lovely spot for a quick meal or a low-key night out. People say this Italian restaurant serves delicious pasta, pizza, and carbonara. They also highlight the attentive staff, cozy atmosphere, and generous portions.

reviews:
[{"rating": 4, "text": "Started at the Bar with Tim. He made me good Espresso Martinis and delivered us great calamari. Went to a table with Marlon. We ordered veal parmesan and chicken picatta they both were flavorful but both overcooked. Bummer to that. Also the burrata was average. We will give it another try in the future. We were near closing time or we would've asked for another dish. Overall great service. Manager present and checking on guests.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "2 months ago", "authorName": "Matt and Jaime G"}, {"rating": 4, "text": "This was our first time dining at Bella Tuscany in Windermere, and we had high hopes walking in‚Äîand for the most part, the food lived up to the hype. The restaurant itself is beautifully set up, cozy, elegant, and perfect for either a romantic date night or a classy meeting with friends or colleagues. The soft lighting, warm tones, and relaxed atmosphere create a setting that feels both upscale and inviting. The ambiance alone sets the tone for what could be a five-star experience.

Let‚Äôs talk about the food, absolutely amazing! Everything we ordered was delicious, but the star of the evening was the massive mozzarella sticks. Honestly, I‚Äôve never seen mozzarella sticks that big and crispy on the outside, gooey and melty inside, full of flavor, and perfectly seasoned. If you go, please do yourself a favor and order those. They‚Äôre a must-have!

We also ordered pasta dishes, and again, the kitchen did not disappoint. I particularly loved the seafood pasta, perfectly cooked pasta, fresh seafood, and a savory sauce that wasn‚Äôt too heavy. The flavors were well-balanced and comforting. The rest of our table also enjoyed their meals, and everyone agreed that the food was excellent.

Unfortunately, where the experience fell flat was in the service department. Our server seemed disengaged and didn‚Äôt come around very often. When I asked for cheese (because who eats pasta without cheese, right?), he returned a while later, stood at the edge of the table and just asked, ‚ÄúDoes anyone want cheese?‚Äù as if he was offering it randomly, not because I specifically requested it. I raised my hand, of course, but it felt awkward and honestly a bit ridiculous. It‚Äôs not a huge thing on its own, but small moments like this can really affect how welcome and attended to a guest feels.

It‚Äôs a shame because the food and setting set the bar high, but the inattentive service lowered the overall experience. I wish I remembered the server‚Äôs name because I don‚Äôt like leaving negative comments without details, but unfortunately I don‚Äôt. That said, with so many top-tier restaurants in the Windermere area, service has to match the quality of the food in order to compete. People don‚Äôt just come out for great meals, they come out to feel cared for and enjoy the whole experience.

Would I go back? Yes! for the food, absolutely. But I hope management takes a closer look at improving staff attentiveness and hospitality. It‚Äôs the missing piece to an otherwise wonderful place. With just a little more attention to customer service, Bella Tuscany could easily be one of the standout Italian restaurants in the area.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "3 months ago", "authorName": "Beatriz Aviles"}, {"rating": 4, "text": "Bella Tuscany is a wonderful place for authentic Italian food. The octopus was tender, and the pasta sauce was perfectly balanced and the service was friendly and attentive. Cozy atmosphere and great for a relaxing mealÔºÅ", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "3 months ago", "authorName": "Basilis Cheng"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "I‚Äôm a lover of this restaurant. Bill (the waiter)and the bar attendants are friendly and always give us good suggestions about food quality combined with a good price. Today, Bill suggested this amazing and tasty snap. Omg‚Ä¶ it is perfect and fresh!", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a month ago", "authorName": "Alba Viana Gomes"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "Cozy Italian restaurant serving all the traditional dishes plus some extras which are features of the house.
The salmon was cooked to perfection and was delicious. The greens on the salad & with the meal could not have tasted fresher.
We enjoyed the house Italian vinaigrette dressing.
Everything was delicious and the service was good.
One suggestion:  the bread with the meal was basically pizza dough-esque. At a restaurant of this caliber, it would be more fitting to offer focaccia or some other more fitting bread selection.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "6 months ago", "authorName": "Elysium Joy"}]

generativeSummary: Low-key eatery dishing up a familiar array of dishes such as butter chicken and chicken tikka massala, plus naan.
reviewSummary:
People say this Indian takeaway offers delicious butter chicken, saag dishes, and chicken kabobs. They also highlight the generous portions, reasonable prices, and convenient online ordering.

Some reviews mention the food can be cold.
reviews:
[{"rating": 5, "text": "We really like the food -- flavorful and well prepared. Since the food is served from the window of a mobile trailer, "service" and "atmosphere" aren't really applicable concepts. But the food is always ready on time, so you could say the service is good. The atmosphere is what you would expect when you stand around in the parking lot outside the trailer.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "in the last week", "authorName": "Nelson Hoffman"}, {"rating": 1, "text": "I was excited to try Indian House on Wheels when it first opened, even though I felt the food was overpriced (nearly $27 for chicken tikka masala, rice, and naan). I decided to give them another chance and ordered the lunch special. Unfortunately, the quality was disappointing ‚Äî the rice was dry, and the garlic naan was cold and crunchy.

But the WORST part: while eating my butter chicken, I found an actual nail in my food. Yes, a metal NAIL you would use in a wall. I immediately called the number listed for the food truck but got no answer. I then called the main India House in Santa Fe, and instead of genuine concern, I felt like they treated me as if I was lying. They asked me to send photos, which I did, but I never received any follow-up or apology.

For both safety and customer service reasons, I cannot recommend this place.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a month ago", "authorName": "BG"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "In response to some other reviews I feel compelled to point out that the home page of their website says in big red letters: "Order Rice and Bread separately it doesn't comes with entrees." And the desktop website allows for custom tip amounts; on mobile you don't see that option but if $5 is too much then you can choose not to tip!
Is their website a little rough around the edges? Yes. Should they warn about the rice in more places (the menu and checkout pages)? Definitely. Do these folks deserve 1 or 2 star reviews for the above problems? Absolutely not. The food is good by Los Alamos standards. I'm sure folks who live here are grateful to have another takeout option, especially one that (can you believe it) is open weekends!", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "3 months ago", "authorName": "Nicolas Capra"}, {"rating": 2, "text": "My goat biryani had shards (small SHARDS) of rib bone - leaving me to excessively chew and then pull out sharp pieces of bone before I swallowed. The meat itself was barely meat - more fascia and fat. The rice in the biryani was not well cooked - some crunchy pieces. Overall, this meal was a 0/0. It was overall so unpleasant I stopped eating it. There goes $20 for nothing‚Ä¶
Which brings me to my husband‚Äôs meal, the butter chicken. The website was very clear that rice & naan is not included, but for the price and the fact that butter chicken, as a dish, is not automatically served with rice‚Ä¶is weird. It‚Äôs like serving a pizza with all the toppings but no crust. The butter chicken was very tasty but was mostly the juice‚Ä¶with some chicken. And again, was >$20 with adding rice separately.

SO DISAPPOINTING.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a month ago", "authorName": "Lindsy Coon"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "Ordered online at 5:18.
Food was ready when I arrived at 5:45.
Had lamb curry medium spice - very good, tender lamb
Also had butter chicken curry - good, tender chicken but I found it too creamy.
Butter Naan was also really big and moist.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "7 months ago", "authorName": "Miel Rim"}]

generativeSummary: Casual eatery specializing in Japanese classics, such as ramen, sushi, poke bowls and rice-based dishes.
editorialSummary: Casual counter-serve chain for health-minded Asian fare from made-to-order sushi rolls to salads.
reviewSummary:
Diners say this restaurant serves up delicious spicy tuna rolls, miso soup, baked salmon rolls, and hand roll boxes packed with salmon. They also highlight the friendly and efficient service, reasonable prices, and clean dining area.

Some reviews mention the staff can be accommodating to dietary restrictions.
reviews:
[{"rating": 5, "text": "We stopped by SanSai Japanese Grill in Burbank and had a great experience! The place is clean, the atmosphere is welcoming, and the staff gave us a warm greeting when we arrived.

We ordered using the kiosk, which was super convenient. It showed pictures of the dishes, so we knew exactly what we were getting. The system was easy to use and even let us customize our ordered, loved that part!

We got the Katsu Sandwich with fries (no veggies) and it was delicious. The fries were nice and crispy, and the sandwich was flavorful. We also had the Philadelphia Roll and some sushi, which were fresh and well-prepared. My favorite was the poke bowl it was outstanding!

Pickup was easy, too they send you updates straight to your phone. Plus, the location is super convenient, right near the airport and perfect for a stop before a flight. We sat outside and enjoyed a relaxing mountain view. Great food, great vibes I‚Äôd definitely come back!", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "3 months ago", "authorName": "Kiwi Mill"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "Great and fast service. Food came out quickly and perfect, I have no complaints. I would totally recommend and come back in the future!", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a week ago", "authorName": "Max Hernandez"}, {"rating": 4, "text": "I've been here a few times for a quick lunch. I had a decent meal at SanSai Japanese Grill and would rate it a solid 4/5. I ordered the Chicken Bowl with a Kale Salad, and while the salad was fresh, crunchy, and had a nice balance of flavors, the chicken left a bit to be desired. It was tender but lacked seasoning, making it feel a little bland. A bit more sauce or spice would've made a big difference.

I also tried the California Roll, which was fresh but unfortunately pretty dull. It didn't have much flavor and felt like it was missing that extra something to make it stand out. While nothing was bad, the flavors just didn't wow me. Despite that, the portions were generous, and everything tasted fresh, making it a good choice for a quick and casual meal. I'd go back, but I'd probably try something different next time!", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "7 months ago", "authorName": "Frank Hernandez"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "Sansai Japanese Grill was a wonderful experience. I ordered the hand roll box. At first I was surprised that it wasn't the rice hand rolls, but more like the cone shaped rolls. However I was then pleasantly surprised with the protein content! Those hand rolls were practically filled to the brim with salmon! There was so much protein in there, I think I got my fish allotment for the whole week. I also tried the EBI eel, however since I have to keep it non-dairy, I didn't realize that it came with coleslaw inside. I took it out and ate the whole thing with a little bit of the kale salad inserted in its place. It was still delicious! However next time I will ask for the eel to not come with the coleslaw. Keep that in mind if you are dairy sensitive like me. The service was exceptional! It's like a five star restaurant. The employee was so wonderful and accommodated all my requests for additional wasabi and ginger. All the employees were kind and professional and waved hello and goodbye. They were all smiling and obviously enjoyed their work environment. The hand rolls were delicious, and really opened me up to a new style of eating sushi. I had only had them one other time before in my life, so this was a very nice experience. I asked the employee if it's OK to bring food from another restaurant in the complex and eat inside and she said that's totally OK since I'm buying a meal from them as well. They're very accommodating and nice people. The bathrooms are clean and well-maintained. The tables are also clean. I will definitely come back, especially because the price was very reasonable. $20 for three hand rolls, miso soup and a delicious kale salad with vinaigrette dressing! You can't beat that. Good job Sansai!", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "7 months ago", "authorName": "Rush Hamden"}, {"rating": 4, "text": "I got the Poke bowl, was good. The ingredients seem fresh and the flavor was as expected.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "2 months ago", "authorName": "Sergio Lopez"}]

reviews:

The Tom Kha soup was equally delicious‚Äîcreamy, tangy, and comforting without being heavy.

Service was quick and extremely friendly, and the vibe is casual but welcoming‚Äîexactly what you want for a pre-beach lunch spot. The only reason this is a 4-star instead of 5? No full bar (I‚Äôm a cocktail lover ‚Äî hence the soju mangotini) Otherwise, Phuket Thai is a must-try if you‚Äôre in South Redondo and craving authentic flavors before heading to the sand.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "2 months ago", "authorName": "Rose"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "Outstanding drinks! The service and food are amazing and it‚Äôs very clean inside!", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "3 weeks ago", "authorName": "Ally Suarez"}, {"rating": 3, "text": "I appreciate diners that offers all day breakfast. With me not being much of an early bird, I don't have to feel the pressure of eating between the normal breakfast hours. Upon entering the diner, I was greeted by the server who led me to an available booth. The diner definitely had that early 80s vibe with retro pictures and signs along the walls. I took a few minutes to overlook the menu as the server came back with my drink. I saw that they have French toast on the menu, but if I wanted anything with it, (eggs, bacon, hash browns, toast, etc) it's an additional charge for each....that's messed up. Not wanting to take up too much time, I ordered the French toast and added eggs...just because.

When the food arrived a few minutes later, I started with the eggs which was scrambled nicely. Added some salt and pepper for flavor and was enjoying every bite. The French toast was alright. It didn't have that cinnamon flavor that I absolutely love and I also noticed that the bread was not coated in egg batter....which is the main part of making French toast.

I originally was gonna give this review two stars, but the eggs was delicious, the service was satisfactory, and the atmosphere was very comfortable. reviews:
[{"rating": 5, "text": "Super cosy spot with huge portions! Everyone who works here is so kind! Thai tea is amazing! Their veg pho is delicious and super soothing but also filling!", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "3 weeks ago", "authorName": "Sofia Sabogal"}, {"rating": 1, "text": "I wish we would have thought to look into parking for our to go pick up order. I drove around for 15 mins looking for parking - of course our food was cold when I got back to the hospital with our order. I also should have stayed at the counter & opened the tied up bag & looked at all of our order to ensure things were good. Our sister who was in the nearby VA Hospital only requested white rice & soy sauce. We ordered that & was specific about getting soy sauce - we didn't receive soy sauce! Bummer! We ordered a few other plates but were super disappointed!  The chicken in the chicken fried rice was not cleaned, meaning I got alot of yucky cartilage, veins, fat & ickyness. My other sis got some straight slices of fat! Yeah, no thanks! üëé üö´", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "2 weeks ago", "authorName": "Beth Williams"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "I travel for work and Pho is a staple in my regular rotation and this one was one of the best. Broth was full of flavor and the steak and brisket were tender. Will definitely be going back", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "2 weeks ago", "authorName": "Erinn"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "I was in coraville for work a few months ago and never tried Saigon. I had to come back this week and ordered it on DoorDash. Everything was spectacular. The  bun Bo hue was spicy and delicious and the broken rice with pork chop was also incredibly good. I have a per diem and didn‚Äôt even get near it. The prices are great and I can‚Äôt say enough about the food and how it was packaged.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "5 months ago", "authorName": "David Levy"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "I have missed authentic Vietnamese food ever since I moved here, but am incredibly happy to report that everything on the menu here feels like it's been pulled right out of Little Saigon in Orange County. As others have mentioned, the service could be a little more attentive, but everyone working there is gracious and welcoming, and we received our entrees very quickly - little things, like offering to-go containers or refilling water, are nothing that can't be improved over time.
The egg rolls here are the best in the city by a mile. Period. My wife, very health-conscious, ordered the stir-fried noodles with chicken not knowing they were crispy, but they arrived light and airy; the vegetables are well seasoned and cooked perfectly; and the sauce is incredibly delicious without being too thick or heavy.
The dish that really sealed my love for this place, though, is the dry vermicelli bowl. It is huge, just like they make it in Westminster. It comes with generous helpings of delicious pork, pork belly, shrimp, a ton of fresh and pickled vegetables, and tasted almost exactly like the food I grew up eating. I agree with other reviewers that there is a definite increased use of sweet chili sauce compared to fish sauce (the most heavily used sauce in Vietnamese cooking), but the entrees here are still delicious.

It's hard to put into words exactly what a restaurant like Saigon's Corner means to me. Yes, the food is great, but for me, it means way more than that. Eating here, for at least a couple hours, made me feel like I was back in California, like I had never left. Cooking is such a huge part of our culture, and out here in the Midwest, it's almost synonymous. It's the reason I hope this business gets all the traffic and support it deserves. Saigon's Corner feels like home. That's the highest praise I can give.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "5 years ago", "authorName": "Justin Chau"}]

I ordered pick up for a few items online including the boneless chicken karahi (I ordered spicy but they will ask), the beef seekh with a side of rice/chickpeas, and extra tandoor naan.

The food took ~40 minutes. When I went inside to pick up my food, the young guys at the counter were very friendly and made a little bit of small talk/banter and the environment was much nicer than I‚Äôd expected from pictures.

The food was all very, very good. The naan was by far some of the best I‚Äôve gotten from any middle eastern restaurant, the chicken karahi was very spicy but flavors were phenomenal, and the seekh was equally great.

My only small complaint is that on the website, the boneless chicken karahi is not listed as a ‚Äúfor 2‚Äù entree so I figured it would be cheaper. It was not, and I ended up paying ~$50 for everything. But it was well worth it!

Would recommend", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "2 months ago", "authorName": "Chandler Thornton"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "Discovered this place a few weeks ago and decided to stop by for dinner with friends. Will come back.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "2 months ago", "authorName": "Zain Malik"}]

As for the food ‚Äî the latte was lukewarm and not what I ordered (I asked for a hot peppermint latte). The bagels weren‚Äôt toasted, and after sitting so long, they were cold by the time I got home. generativeSummary: Cozy BBQ diner featuring spare ribs, brisket, pulled pork, and other smoked meats.
editorialSummary: Family-owned business with smoked meats, including beef ribs & brisket, from a mobile service.
reviewSummary:
People say this barbecue restaurant serves delicious brisket, ribs, and smoked corn. They also highlight the friendly staff, clean interior, and chill atmosphere.

Other reviews mention the food can be overpriced.
reviews:
[{"rating": 5, "text": "Ambiance: Rustic & clean BBQ spot with an amazing selection of meat plates, sides, and sandwiches! Fast and friendly service. Incredibly welcoming atmosphere, seemed many customers were returning patrons who knew the staff- something you rarely see these days!

The Mac & cheese was delicious! Every side we ordered was very good. Highly recommend the smoked corn. The brisket was tender and a delicious flavor. Parking onsite. Food was brought out quickly despite being fairly busy for a Friday post-lunch crowd. Highly recommend Gatlin's!", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "4 months ago", "authorName": "MeetWithMacey"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "I had to try this place after seeing the chef/owner on BBQ Brawl. It did not disappoint! Brisket was the best I‚Äôve had in Texas, house sausage was the best sausage I‚Äôve ever had, dirty rice was bomb, and candied yams were amazing. I‚Äôll be making a stop every time I‚Äôm in Houston.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a week ago", "authorName": "Anthony Martin"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "Found this place through the food network show BBQ brawl. When celebrity chefs endorse a restaurant it is imperative to try it. I was glad I found this place in Houston, TX. The raspberry habanero wings were perfectly smoked and extremely flavourful without being ridiculously spicy. The pulled pork was juicy and tender. The portion size is massive and I was able to get two meals out of it. Highly recommend for anyone visiting Houston. The reason I gave four stars for the atmosphere is because the seats were not comfortable. A minor headache one can overlook over the wonderful food and staff.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "2 months ago", "authorName": "Varun Chandrashekaran"}, {"rating": 4, "text": "This restaurant was on our list to try while in Houston. My family and I all ordered the ribs with sides (collard greens, Mac & cheese, dirty rice). The ribs were good but better with the sauce that came on the side. The Mac & Cheese was cheesy but not flavorful, the dirty rice was good, and the collard greens had spice but not flavorful.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "3 months ago", "authorName": "Na‚ÄôSha Palmer"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "Ordered brisket (flat), spare ribs (St Louis cuts), and back ribs. All three were enjoyable.

Brisket was perfectly trimmed, seasoned, and smoked. Meat was tender, though slightly dry. Not the top tier that I had from other places, but certainly delicious.

Back ribs were delicious. Well seasoned and cooked. The outside was a bit crunchy, probably because being under open fire for too long, while inside was fall of the bone. So after all, I liked them.

Spare ribs seemed to be cooked first then trimmed the tip flap away, turning the ribs to St Louis style. Seasoning/flavor was very good. The meat was cooked slightly under fall-off-the-done tenderness. Cartilage was still tough to bite down though eatable. I wish  they could be cooked a bit longer.

Overall, this is a 30-dollar meal, having three meats in good portions. Seasoning/trimming/cooking were all well done by the pitmaster, in my opinion. Highly recommend.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "3 weeks ago", "authorName": "Nicolin Chen"}]

locationName: American Way Smokehouse - Kansas City BBQ
reviewSummary: People say this restaurant serves delicious brisket, pulled pork sandwiches, and burnt ends. They highlight the amazing sauce, tender meat, and excellent bite of the ribs. They also like the great atmosphere and friendly staff.
reviews:
[{"rating": 4, "text": "We stopped in for lunch and had a great experience overall. The atmosphere was welcoming, and the service was top-notch ‚Äî friendly and attentive. We ordered the burnt ends, sausage, and pulled pork, with mac ‚Äòn‚Äô cheese and beans on the side.
The sausage was pretty standard for a BBQ spot. The burnt ends were a bit too fatty for my taste ‚Äî some folks might love that, but I prefer a more balanced meat-to-fat ratio. The pulled pork was good, though a few bites were a little on the bland side.
The real standouts were the beans and the cookies ‚Äî absolutely delicious! I‚Äôll definitely be back to try more of the menu. Worth the visit!", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a month ago", "authorName": "steven shadduck"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "Great food. They deserve the rating.

The burnt ends are some of the best and maybe the best I've had in KC. Pulled pork was excellent and just right. Texas toast was good too. The baked beans were fantastic with good seasoning, some onions, and a lot of meat.

All meats had great smoke flavor.

Three recommendations:
1. Need sweet tea at a BBQ joint in KC. Adding sugar to cold tea doesn't work and isn't the same.
2. The brisket was a bit overdone and just a little on the dry side. The smoke was on point though.
3. Mac and cheese was a little bit on the watery side but was still excellent.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "2 weeks ago", "authorName": "Taj Jones"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "American Way Smokehouse is a hidden gem in Independence. The smoked meats are incredibly tender and juicy‚Äîwhether it‚Äôs brisket, burnt ends, or pulled pork, every bite is packed with rich, smoky flavor. The sides are just as impressive: the Backyard Beans are hearty and delicious with chunks of meat.

What really sets this place apart is the attention to detail. You can tell everything is made with care, from the house-made sauces to the fresh-baked cookies in the bakery. The staff is friendly and welcoming, and the cozy, patriotic atmosphere makes it feel like home.

Whether you‚Äôre grabbing lunch or treating friends to a casual dinner, this spot delivers every time. Highly recommend!", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "in the last week", "authorName": "Jeremy Sellars"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "Stopped by on a recommendation from a friend. Ordered the rib plate for 2. It had a slab of ribs 2 sides and toast. $30.00 I had the beans they were very good! My husband had the coleslaw and didn't care for it. The ribs were very meaty. It was more than enough for 2. The sauces were excellent üëå The staff was very friendly and helpful. We will be back again for great BBQ!", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "2 weeks ago", "authorName": "marie wyly"}, {"rating": 4, "text": "Picked this up the other night figuring I would try somewhere new. The bbq is really good, a little sweet but very tender without a lot of fat.
I gave 4 stars because there were a couple of things that weren‚Äôt so great.
While I was at the register paying for my food the manager took a taste of some meat with his fingers. Nothing we haven‚Äôt all done at home, and not a deal breaker for me.
The other thing was the caramel drizzled sugar cookie. It was AWFUL. I think an ingredient  or two was left out.
It was a baking soda flavored cookieüòù.
The chocolate chip cookie was good( no picture proves that) but the sugar cookie was a lie.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a week ago", "authorName": "Michele BT"}]

generativeSummary: Casual eatery dishing up barbecue offerings such as ribs and pulled pork, plus mac ‚Äôn‚Äô cheese.
reviewSummary:
Diners say this barbecue restaurant serves up delicious brisket, ribs, and smoked wings with peach tea BBQ sauce, alongside standout sides like sweet potato cornbread, collard greens, and mac and cheese. They also highlight the friendly and attentive staff, and the welcoming atmosphere with indoor and outdoor dining options.

Some reviews mention the food can be pricey.
reviews:
[{"rating": 2, "text": "This is a 5-star BBQ restaurant for people WHO DON‚ÄôT EAT BBQ REGULARLY. If you just want meat cooked by fire with no flavor or finesse and feel like taking a picture, this place is for you. I know what you‚Äôre thinking: the guy on TikTok said it was amazing, and that one girl on Instagram said it was rated top 50 BBQ in the nation. The pictures make the meat look good. I‚Äôm here to tell you the meat ‚Äúlooks great,‚Äù BUT IT IS absolutely flavorless‚Äînot even a pinch of salt or smoke to the meat. You absolutely need every bit of BBQ sauce to give this food flavor, AND even then, ask yourself: did you pay 50 to 100 dollars TO GO SAUCE TASTING!? On to the positives: the mac and cheese was perfect, and the service was excellent as well. But you didn‚Äôt go to a BBQ place for cheese noodles and conversation‚Äîyou went for meat, and I‚Äôm here to tell you they don‚Äôt have it. Take your money and your time to Green Street Meats, where every bite is flavorful. If you‚Äôre going to pay for BBQ, do it the right way.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a week ago", "authorName": "Christian Andrew"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "A must try, but go early because the food will run out.  That's how good it is.  There was no chicken products when we got there.  They do announce it.  The line was near the door, not too bad for a rainy day.  The line moved pretty fast, about 15 minutes or less from the door entryway.  I purchased the Texas Trio which is:  beef brisket, 4-5 rib bones with meat of course, sausage, and bread.  I don't know why I didn't get the pickles and the pickled onions. I love that.  They show that in the picture. Maybe you have to ask for it.  Also I think you have to ask for a site of sauce because I didn't have any in the bag.  I took mine to go.  My husband got the whole slab, baked beans, and fries.  I got the corn elote, and the sweet potato cornbread, deliciousness! The meat was tender. The taste was delicious.  I love the brisket. The very best. The sausage was a little spicy but delicious. The corn, great tasting, and the sweet potato cornbread oh my God it's delicious and goes really good with your food.  If you want to eat there, there's an inside and the outside area.  I forgot yesterday was Sweetest Day so that's probably why they ran out of food yesterday.  Also, they probably ran out because it's so delicious.  You definitely have to try it. Be prepared to pay a little bit more than you would at your local barbecue joint.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a week ago", "authorName": "Deborah Sawyer"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "I came in today around 11:45 am and it was crowded. But the line went fast and they were very efficient !!!

My mom will be 80 years old in January....With family roots from Crystal Springs, Mississippi and she said these were the best pork ribs she's ever had! I agree! We each got a half a slab! They were sooooo good I forgot to take a picture of them! Mannnnnnn soooo sooo tender! Amazing Sanders! We loved it. We also got Mac and Cheese, and Collard Greens which were delicious! Mac and cheese and collards for $6 for a small side and $10 for a large. Very reasonably priced! The large is massive and can feed 3-4 people.

Now the sweet potato cornbread looked amazing visually but fell flat for my mom and I. You have the sugar and the cinnamon, and the butter covering the top of the cornbread and then the sweet potato is kind of layered in the cornbread mix. I think it would taste better if you took some of that topping and put it actually in the cornbread not just on top. Also try roasting the sweet potatoes to kinda give it  more flavor. Well at least for my taste lolllllll! However, my son LOVED it!

Customer service was amazing, washrooms were clean and for you guys to be busy, the food came out pretty fast!!! You guys deserve five stars!!!! I can't wait to try the other things on the menu. Great job Sanders BBQ! Ya'll better workkkk!

***** Sorry I didn't get a picture of my own ribs, they were so good I smashed them before I could! But as they were making someone's plate, I took a picture of a sampler of some sort because it had sausage and ribs on the plate too!

*****Oh and they are cashless!", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "in the last week", "authorName": "Naiima Dandridge"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "As you can see, I took on a lot of food!!!
The ribs ‚Äî amazing! The sauce wasn‚Äôt poured on top; it was coated on the ribs, and you gotta get them.

Next, the brisket ‚Äî I‚Äôm a fan of fatty brisket, and yes, the flavor is there. It‚Äôs not really my type, but the flavor still hits.

The mac and cheese? THICK and packed with flavor, especially if you can get the crust/top ‚Äî OMG!

Now the oxtails‚Ä¶ huge portions! You get two types: fatty and meaty. I even got a smaller one too. Not everyone likes the fat, but I do! Eat them alone or save them for last, because you will get sleepy after the oxtails ‚Äî trust me.

The cornbread (not pictured) is very sweet ‚Äî I just got it by itself, no greens.

Yes, Sanders is a must try! But don‚Äôt do it alone ‚Äî you‚Äôll need help, this is a lot of food!

I‚Äôll definitely be back for greens, sweet potato, and cornbread ‚Äî then mix those oxtails right in with it.

The wings were good too ‚Äî and the fries? Dip them in that BBQ sauce for a perfect kick!", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "2 weeks ago", "authorName": "Trell019"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "I'm a New Englander and spent my birthday visiting my son in Chicago. He and his fiance told me they had to take me to the best BBQ place in Chicago. We had ribs, catfish and the peach tea wings with collards, mac n cheese and sweet potato cornbread! OMG! They were right. That was the best BBQ ribs and (fried perfectly) catfish I've ever had in a restaurant.  And the sweet potato cornbread was off the hizzy! The wings were tasty and enjoyably tender, so were the ribs.
I was very pleased. I told friends and family that if they're ever in the Chicago area to be sure to check out Sanders. The only downfall is you may have to endure a long line, but trust me, it'll  be worth it. Happy eating", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "3 weeks ago", "authorName": "Tammie Streeter"}]

reviewSummary: People say this Vietnamese restaurant serves delicious pho, vermicelli bowls, and egg rolls. They highlight the generous portions, flavorful broths, and crispy, light egg rolls. They also like the fast and efficient service, and the friendly and attentive staff.
reviews:
[{"rating": 5, "text": "My girlfriend loves this place, especially the eggrolls. She‚Äôs quite picky with pho, too, so this hits the spot for her.

The pho broth is great. Doesn‚Äôt taste bland, sweet, or like it has too much msg. They also had chili oil!! I am one of those who loves chili oil in my pho, so this got me super excited. Only problem was that it wasn‚Äôt really tasty. Just simply tasted like chili and oil, no aromatics or additional flavor. The eggrolls were extremely delicious with such a crispy/crunchy texture. I‚Äôd say one of the best I‚Äôve had at a restaurant for sure! Although, I still don‚Äôt know if I can agree on the price at $15.50. I‚Äôd assume it is due to the difficulty of preparing and the complimentary herbs/lettuce, but each to their own on that opinion.

Service was extremely quick and food came out extremely fast for the two bowls of pho and eggrolls. Water was always topped off before I get a chance to notice and I drink a lot of water. Definitely a 10/10 on that, too!

We will be back when we‚Äôre in the area again! Thank you :)", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "4 months ago", "authorName": "Bill Vang"}, {"rating": 1, "text": "No service for take out. They just want you to in and out. It‚Äôs fine as long as food is good. I came here because of the high reviews but man the meat in the pho was like rubber. I had to throw away almost all the meat. What a waste!", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "2 months ago", "authorName": "Lily Wang"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "Definitely one of the best Vietnamese restaurants around. Be ready for a wait if you are going on Saturday for lunch, the space is limited and it gets packed. It is worth the wait though, the food is delicious and authentic. The number 44 Bun Chao Tom comes with their signature egg rolls that deserve the praise. Staff are friendly and helpful and food come quickly.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "7 months ago", "authorName": "Shawn Sheng"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "Update: Still the GOAT!

Update: The best there was, there is, and ever shall be.

Update: The top #1 pho place hands down. No comparison! The best of the best!

Top 3 pho places of all time hands down. Pho is superb. Pork chops are superb. The owners and all the employees are superb. The #1 Pho w/ everything is a nice portion of meat and noodles for about $17. The Cha Gio egg rolls are hands down the best in town and I will dare to say in Los Angeles and LA county! I would avoid weekends bc its crazy busy on weekends.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "4 months ago", "authorName": "Stephen Lee"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "We've gotten a bit picky about pho since we went to Vietnam a couple of times and find many of the pho we try in the US not as flavorful as we'd like, but this was the best we've had in a long time. We both had a pho tai and split the cha gio. The fried spring rolls were delicious, fairly big, and came with all the herbs and vegetables you could want. This is definitely our new go-to for pho!
The staff were friendly and the meal was very efficient. It's a busy place. We went around 5:45 on a Friday and we're seated immediately but when we came back out about 40min later, there were groups waiting outside.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "6 months ago", "authorName": "Steph Couvrette"}]

generativeSummary: Laid-back restaurant for pho noodles, vermicelli salads and boba tea, plus classic Vietnamese dishes, all prepared with quality ingredients.

reviews:
[{"rating": 5, "text": "One thing about it! This will ALWAYS be my favorite spot for a good pho! I got the large steak and brisket which I can always get 2 servings out of ! Hits the spot every time! Super friendly staff. I was offered something to drink while i waited too. Awesome!", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a month ago", "authorName": "Binta Thomas"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "Food was great, and service was even better! They were very welcoming and attentive. My sister and I had the Pho - no meat with the chicken broth, very yummy and they let me have extra sprouts at no charge! The fried dumplings were also delish, though I think I'd prefer soy sauce to the dipping sauce they provided, which was a spin on it.

I learned the owners are very involved in the community! Which is very refreshing, I'm pretty sure it was the owner/husband that visited our table twice to check in.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "3 months ago", "authorName": "Katlyn Fohn"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "Today was my first time visiting this restaraunt and I've got to say it was the most pleasant experience I've had in a very long time! The atmosphere is very relaxing and all of the staff members i encountered where very kind and attentive. I will definitely be back again to enjoy the awesome customer service and food!", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "in the last week", "authorName": "Dyan Youngblood"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "The broccoli and tofu stir fry was delicious - I loved the marinated + fried tofu, it was crispy and flavored. The food is decent, just not what I would consider traditional Vietnamese.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "7 months ago", "authorName": "Binh Nguyen"}]

reviews:
[{"rating": 5, "text": "Good portion of food for great price, I'd recommend most of the food (vegetarian bowl, lamb shish roll up, pistachio baklava) except for bland moussaka side.

If you decide to dine in, please note they give you a meze for one with 4 dips and 2 big pitas. We didn't realize and took it home, so yum! Lots of seats, we plan to bring friends next time!", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "2 months ago", "authorName": "Donne N."}, {"rating": 5, "text": "We went to Boston Kebap for dine-in and really enjoyed our experience. Definitely a place we‚Äôll be coming back to!", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a month ago", "authorName": "Melda Meryem DAGLI"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "From the moment we arrived, we were greeted with genuine warmth and attentive service. The dishes were brought out promptly, and the complimentary hummus and tea were gracious touches that added to the charm of the experience. With generous seating and a calm, inviting atmosphere, the establishment offers a truly enjoyable setting for a meal.

That said, there were a couple of drawbacks worth noting: the entrance door was left open during our visit, allowing cigarette smoke from those gathered outside to filter into the dining area, which slightly diminished the otherwise pleasant ambiance.

Additionally, the absence of pricing on the menu was a point of discomfort, as it made ordering feel less transparent.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "5 months ago", "authorName": "Arrecis"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "Amazing Service and Great Food!

I always enjoy coming here ‚Äî highly recommend it!", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "2 weeks ago", "authorName": "Manar Altekreeti"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "Tremendous variety of amazing foods. The Doner roll is fantastic, the tabbouleh is flavorful, the moussaka is to die for.

reviewSummary: People say this restaurant serves delicious Lebanese food, including babaganoush, falafel, kebabs, and pitza. They highlight the fresh pita bread, flavorful dips like muhammara and labneh, and the cozy, welcoming atmosphere. They also like the friendly and attentive service.
reviews:
[{"rating": 5, "text": "This was a great little Lebanese place with all of their seats full. The service is very friendly. We ordered babaghanoush to start with - it was a perfect smoky flavor that I was looking for. The pita was just made and it was very good and hot (they do charge extra for it but it is worth it). The lamb kebab sandwich was very good and had a lot of lamb. It was extraordinary and fresh. The same goes for falafel sandwich.

Recommend it 100% !!!", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a month ago", "authorName": "Artem Bakatov"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "It‚Äôs a nice cozy restaurant with tasty Mediterranean food options‚Ä¶ the pita bread served is so fresh and light, paired with hummus, muhammara and labneh‚Ä¶ the kebabs and falafel is tasty and nice dessert.. it‚Äôs definitely one of the great options for Mediterranean..", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "3 months ago", "authorName": "Torrence Innocent Daniel's"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "This was a quaint little spot that full of life and every chair was full, that was a great sign. Once we were seated the host was very friendly, we order 3 entrees, 2 glasses of wine to start. Must say this was the best Moussaka I‚Äôve ever had, really I can‚Äôt rave enough about it!!! The Chicken Pitza with lemon, garlic, red pepper, scallion, and parsley was also very fresh and tasty. The Merguez lamb sausage plate was also delicious, would also rave it was also the best I‚Äôve ever had anywhere. For desert we slit the Muhalabia which is a milk flan with a rasberry reduction, this also was divine with some Turkish Coffee. This Lebanese food was worth returning I really enjoyed Moustache it‚Äôs a New York fit 100%", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "5 months ago", "authorName": "Gothic Hangman"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "YUMM! Such a great find and I can't wait to return to try their other items. Ordered the muhammara, hummus, the chicken kebab plate, and pitas.

Everything was made fresh to order and the pitas came out piping hot! Very generous serving size and lovely staff :)", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "2 weeks ago", "authorName": "A Zhang"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "Very delicious chicken kebab, many of the dishes taste like a long standing family recipe that has been perfected over decades.

If you enjoy deeply rich onion and garlic flavor on legumes you must try the mujaddara. I tried the mujaddara in 2022, and I‚Äôve come back to eat it every trip to NYC since. To all my fellow Egyptians - it tastes similar to a tomato sauce-less koshari in the best way possible.

If I lived in NYC I‚Äôd be here at least once a week", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a month ago", "authorName": "Malak Hmimy"}]

The wings are less expensive than wingstop and are usually cooked correctly.

I've gotten 10 different sauces now.  In my opinion, all their sauces/rubs are under flavored.

reviewSummary: People say this pizza restaurant serves delicious cheesesteaks, pizza, and fries. They highlight the generous portions, fresh ingredients, and the value of the lunch special. They also like the warm and friendly atmosphere, and the attentive and welcoming staff.
reviews: [{"rating": 5, "text": "Crazy good! First of all, I want to make it clear that I do not own this establishment, I don‚Äôt know anyone who works there, and I do not get compensated to write this review in anyway. However, I am a well schooled and well traveled person who has eaten all over the world ‚Äì and it doesn‚Äôt get any better than PIZZA VILLAGE! I did some research online to find a good place that was close to the tubing spot (Bucks County River Country) where my friends and I went tubing today. After we went tubing, we came to PIZZA VILLAGE. From the outside~one could easily mistake this place for just your average pizza joint on a strip mall. Oh! But you‚Äôd be SOOOOO wrong!\nWhere shall I begin? We were greeted by Stephanie behind the counter, and she was really nice and warm. Then the gentlemen that were making the pizzas were also really nice. We sat down and ordered off the menu. Stephanie made sure we all had a very nice glass of ice water with lemon as we perused the menus. We ordered two garden salads, zucchini sticks, fried calamari, an order of french fries, and a large cheese pan pizza. Stephanie brought us over to show us all the different types and styles of pizzas that they make, and they all looked delicious ‚Äì yet we went with the pan pizza because it looked like a deep dish style, and it made all our mouths water. The salads were quite large and made with really nice Romain lettuce, all types of veggies, and let me just say that they use the best blue cheese dressing I think I‚Äôve ever had. It had huge chunks of blue cheese in it, and I could‚Äôve eaten it with a spoon. The salads both came with two piping hot croissant shaped dinner rolls which we all devoured because they were off the hook yum! The french fries were cooked deliciously perfect ‚Äì crispy and light. They even serve the more expensive Heinz Ketchup which doesn‚Äôt have the high fructose corn syrup.  Nice touch, and much appreciated! The calamari was tender and delicious as was it‚Äôs accompanying marinara sauce.  Now for the pan pizza‚Ä¶omg! Crust was cooked so perfectly. I‚Äôm smiling as I write this just remembering how delicious it was! It was lightly crispy on the undercarriage bottom and yet chewy just the way you want it. The edges around the crust were so frickin‚Äô delicious I couldn‚Äôt believe it. The cheese, the sauce, forgetaboutit! I made the comment to my friends that if we were in a five star very expensive restaurant with linen tablecloths and candlelight, and they served this food, we would be absolutely delighted, and yet here it was being served at this very, very reasonably priced down to earth spot. The entire time Stephanie was so attentive and helpful and kind~she is just amazing! So are the guys cooking! We all chatted and all I can tell you is this place is filled with skill and love~need I say more? Frankly, I can‚Äôt wait to go tubing again just to come back to PIZZA VILLAGE.  I want to try everything on the menu! I noticed a sign that said they serve fish and chips, and I can‚Äôt wait to try it ‚Äì I‚Äôm sure it‚Äôs going to be delicious! (FYI‚Ä¶ My nephew was with us today, and he manages one of the most successful and popular high end restaurants in Philadelphia and he completely agreed that everything was off the charts great at PIZZA VILLAGE!).", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "2 months ago", "authorName": "Joseph John Brunetti"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "We love Pizza Village! They have the best Drunken Brooklyn pizza around, hands down! I‚Äôve also had their salads- so good. Big portions and very fresh. They‚Äôve catered for my daughter‚Äôs sports teams and it‚Äôs always delicious and on time. The staff there is welcoming and kind. Highly recommend!", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "3 weeks ago", "authorName": "Jessica Jackson"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "I just got the first time went to village pizza. Great place to relax and enjoy delicious food! People were friendly and served me table side. I ordered a steak with fried unions and a pizza. They were fast and the food was served hot and very fresh. Had a great experience. I will be going back for this fantastic tasting food! As I was leaving I met the owner I assumed Nick. He was A cool guy asked me how it was and was very personable. Can‚Äôt wait to go again. I highly recommend this place", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "6 months ago", "authorName": "Anthony stephens"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "Delicious thin crust. Cozy atmosphere. Definitely will visit back when in Doylestown.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a week ago", "authorName": "Al"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "We love indulging in our weekend pizza outings, and one of our favorite spots is Pizza Village. The atmosphere is always warm and inviting, complemented by the friendliest staff who make everyone feel right at home. The pizza is outstanding, featuring a perfect blend of gooey cheese and flavorful toppings, while the salads are fresh and delightful, providing a refreshing balance. With an extensive menu to choose from, you can enjoy a whole pie or grab a delicious slice, making it a great destination for any pizza lover!", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "8 months ago", "authorName": "ThingamaGeorge"}]

generativeSummary: Eatery specializing in pizza and wings, this casual spot also boasts TVs for viewing sporting events.
reviewSummary:
People say this pizza restaurant serves great buffalo chicken, nice appetizers, and good fries. They also highlight the delicious cheese bread, flavorful wings, and great service.

Other reviews mention the wings can be small.
reviews:
[{"rating": 3, "text": "Pizza was delicious! And pick up time was on time! But the wings we got‚Ä¶. Pretty upset with. The size we got I wouldn‚Äôt even call them wings. Barely any meat on them and I will NOT be buying them again. If they are fine with serving people wings this big, I‚Äôm not okay with that. I work in the restaurant business and I would never serve these to anyone this small.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "2 months ago", "authorName": "Marlee Myers"}, {"rating": 1, "text": "I'd heard people talk about this place for a while, so I finally decided to give it a try. What a letdown.

We ordered the wings, which are supposedly what they're known for. I was honestly shocked when they came out. The bone in wings were tiny. I'm not exaggerating. They were laughably small, like parakeet wings. For the price, it felt like a total rip off.

We also got a pizza, and it was just a sea of grease. The whole top was slick, and the crust underneath was tough and chewy. It just tasted cheap. We also tried the nachos, which was literally just a tray of plain chips from a bag and a tiny little cup of cold cheese sauce on the side.

The place itself felt run down, and the service was slow. Maybe we just caught them on a "bad night," as I've heard, but I'm not risking my money again to find out. I don't get the hype at all.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "in the last week", "authorName": "Jordan Dotson"}, {"rating": 4, "text": "Food here was pretty good. We had wings and pizza. Priced about like everything else in this category. Has a gaming room connected to it.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "4 months ago", "authorName": "Eric Wilcox"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "Went to Mister B's before the Thunderbolts hockey game on 2/9. Arrived and was seated quickly. I personally had never eaten at either location of Mister B's.
We ordered a couple appetizers. We did the pick 3 we chose fried pickles, mushrooms and mozzarella bread. Also ordered breadsticks and two different flavors of wings (not pictured forgot to take a picture of them). Also ordered was a super deluxe XL thin crust pizza. I really liked the pickles they are thin  pickles not the thicker ones the mozzarella breadsticks were good as well. The only thing I did not like was the nacho cheese it was just on the thin side. The wings were good and nicely cooked. The pizza was really good. I really enjoyed that the toppings were on the pizza evenly and the crust was nice and crisp. We did order drinks beer and a strawberry lemonade with vodka which as SUPER good I could drink those all day long.

Service was good the server checked on us many times and knew when we were done and offered boxes without us even asking. We made it to the game on time. Very pleased with the length of time it took for the food to come out. There wasn't a long wait for anything after putting our order in.  And the left over pizza heated up well in the air fryer the next day. Definitely will come back and try some other things.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a year ago", "authorName": "April"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "We used go to Mr. B'S Henderson but always crowded hardly any parking slow service. Loud atmosphere.  Slow food. Only thing fast was Sodas. Used a credit card for food left cash for tip. Waitress I guess Didn't  think tip wasn't enough and added a 50.00 tip. Surprising enough wife caught it back. It was only 30.00 food bill. Manager said he couldn't understand it was one of there best waitresses Go Figure. But completely happy with Evansville location. And with the Owensboro location.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a month ago", "authorName": "DENNIS ALTHOFF"}]

reviewSummary: People say this fast food restaurant serves delicious burgers, chicken tenders, and Nashville hot chicken sandwiches. They highlight the crispy fries, flavorful sauces, and generous portions, as well as the affordable prices and clean atmosphere. They also like the friendly staff and quick service.
reviews:
[{"rating": 5, "text": "This is a great spot for vegetarians! They fry the paneer and fries in separate oil from the chicken. The paneer burger has a great kick to it and nice spice level if you ask for it. And the fries are out of this world! Great atmosphere and service too, highly recommend!", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a month ago", "authorName": "Keval Sojitara"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "I love hot chicken so I was so glad I came across Zanders in Somerset! We ended up trying a bunch of different items but my favorite has to be the Chicken Loaded Mac n Cheese! They even have a lot of vegetarian alternatives for almost everything on their menu!!", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "2 months ago", "authorName": "Eesha"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "Came here for lunch on a rainy Wednesday afternoon. Place wasn‚Äôt packed. Had one guy cooking & working the register.

Ordered the 2 pc tenders w/ fries & a side of Mac & cheese.

The food was great. A lot of flavor. Tenders were fried perfectly.

Would definitely recommend", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "2 months ago", "authorName": "Maurice Hayes"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "Not gonna lie, I been eyeballing this place every day and I finally went in and without hesitation and without any remorse, I got the extra spicy Nashville Hot chicken sandwich. Having lived in Nashville, Korea, and even attending the secrets of these recipes as a class, I found this to be impeccably delicious. The zest sauce had a bit too much on the sandwich, but other than that it was perfection.

Mac and cheese wasn't bad either! Fully recommend!", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "5 months ago", "authorName": "Matt M (TranqX)"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "I recently visited Zanders with my family, and it was an awesome experience. The kids absolutely loved the French fries‚Äîcrispy and perfectly seasoned, they couldn't stop munching on them! For myself, I tried the Nashville Hot Chicken Sandwich and the Waffle Hot Chicken Sandwich, and both were absolutely amazing. The flavors were spot on, and the heat from the Nashville Hot Chicken was just right for my taste buds.

For the Fried Chicken, I went with a spicy level, and it was perfect‚Äîexactly the heat I enjoy. Every bite was delicious! The highlight, though, was definitely the banana pudding. It was hands down the best I‚Äôve ever had‚Äîrich, creamy, and perfectly sweet.

Also, the chicken pictures on the wall were too much fun! It added such a playful vibe to the place, making the atmosphere even more enjoyable. On top of that, I got a 25% discount, which made the meal even better. Highly recommend Zanders for anyone craving delicious comfort food and a great time with family!", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "8 months ago", "authorName": "Sam Ghani"}]

generativeSummary: Casual spot for juicy chicken dishes in fried or Nashville hot variations and cocktails.
editorialSummary: Hip, contemporary fast-food outpost for fried chicken, including Nashville hot sandwiches.
reviews:
[{"rating": 4, "text": "This place! So far, favorite fried chicken place in South Orange County! Medium spice is hot (getting mild next time), the loaded fries are WAFFLE fries, and sauces are good. Great portion sizes, and lots of outside seating.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "in the last week", "authorName": "Keith Bachman"}, {"rating": 2, "text": "Salty. Very very salty. I wanted to like this place. One night I saw the owners come in and do a deep cleaning and was impressed by that so I made it a point to try this place.

Well. Loaded fries were a load of salt and the sauce was oily or?? Tasted like mayonnaise with an attempt at seasoning. Very heavy.

Ps. It‚Äôs time again for the deep cleaning especially your soda machine filters.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "7 months ago", "authorName": "dan s"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "Best fried chicken I've ever had in my life and I've traveled all over. Cluck has juicy, flavorful chicken. I love that the Nashville hot is actually insanely spicy. I don't love their sauces and I do think it's a bit over priced for a fast food restaurant but it's so good. I always stop by here anytime in in OC. I love the nugget meal and the waffle fries are fire. I've introduced this place to so many ppl.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "2 months ago", "authorName": "Alizeh Zahidi"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "We arrived at John Wayne airport and headed directly to Cluck Kitchen for lunch.  The chicken sandwiches here are pretty life-changing.  I got the Nashville Hot chicken sandwich.  The chicken for this is perfectly cooked and seasoned.  The breast was almost an inch thick, but it was tender and tempting with every bit.  The first two bites, you think that the bun is going to be too much, but you soon realize that you need that heavy-duty bun to have it stand up to the juice of this sandwich.

The staff at the register warned us that their flavors tend to the hot side, so since it was my first time here I got the mild. I was thankful that she had pointed this out because it was plenty warm.

I also ordered some of the street corn fritters.  Compared to the chicken they did not have the same level of flavor, and I would recommend picking up an extra cup of sauce to dip the fritters in.  The cups of sauce cost an extra 75 cents, but I think it would have really added to the fritters.  The fritters are light and fluffy.

We ate outside in the large shared dining area and it was very pleasant.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "3 years ago", "authorName": "Steven Yackel"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "Great chicken and biscuit, the fried pickles were also tasty. The atmosphere wasn‚Äôt the greatest but being able to eat outside made up for it.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "7 months ago", "authorName": "Spencer Harris"}]

reviews:
[{"rating": 5, "text": "Ever since we moved here in 2018, this has been a go-to place for YEARS. The Employees & owners are nice and great people. Never had an issue with customer service.

The food is top notched & is well worth the money as well as the variety is good.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a week ago", "authorName": "jay allen"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "I was pleasantly surprised by the cleanliness, food quality, food freshness and overall presentation of the meal. This place is really a hidden gem, this is my new go to spot to get my fried chicken, Flounder over rice and and wedges are really amazing . And people at the cashier are very helpful in choosing the food from their menu .Trust me you will not be disappointed", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a year ago", "authorName": "dhruthi palakurthi"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "I ordered the shrimp skewers...omg they were so delicious and seasoned on point. My mom ordered the wings w/okra they looked good as well. Great place to try, called in my order got there and it was ready! No complaints here!", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a month ago", "authorName": "Phatnjuicey Alldatime"}, {"rating": 4, "text": "It was my first time purchasing food from this carryout establishment. The gentleman who took my order was pleasant and explained the menu options to me very clearly. The restaurant was small and didn't have much space. People were standing around waiting for their orders to be called out, so I went to sit in the car. They told me my order would be ready in 15 minutes, and that was pretty accurate.

The total amount for my order was very pricy ($45.43), but I didn't question it. I paid for it, and that was that. I ordered the chicken, lamb, and shrimp platter that came with a small side salad and rice. Once I went back to receive my order, the guy who took my order stated that they had overcharged me by mistake and refunded the additional money ($15.14) back to my card. That was very honorable and showed integrity on their part.

I did question the fact that since they are Muslims and Hallal, why would they be serving shrimp? I didn't think they'd do that, but I could be wrong. Lastly, I got home and opened the container, and everything smelled and looked good. I tasted it. It was good and seasoned just right. I will definitely go back again to try their fried fish and fried chicken as well. I suggest you give them a try.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a month ago", "authorName": "Nubian Bruh"}, {"rating": 4, "text": "While in #charlotte NC, stopped at US Fries Chicken, they have multiple locations across the city. wanted to go with something fast, easy and simple, and this spot has it all. we ordered a few items like the Chopped Cheese, Gyros Wrap, and Chicken Tenders. overall we enjoyed the food, favorite item was the Chopped Cheese, perfectly seasoned, fresh, and generous with the portion.

generativeSummary: Casual eatery for flavorful Mediterranean kabobs, including juicy-meat and vegetarian options.
reviewSummary: People say this Mediterranean restaurant serves delicious kabobs, including chicken, beef, and lamb, as well as gyros, hummus, and fresh salads. They highlight the generous portions, fresh ingredients, and flavorful seasoning. They also like the clean and modern atmosphere, and the friendly and attentive staff.
reviews:
[{"rating": 4, "text": "Food wise, very great. The meats are seasoned to bring out the best in each meat and the cooking on each is also perfection. The lamb was phenomenal. The portions are generous (personally I get 1-2 portions per meal) with balancing side dishes. The side dishes allow for a smoother experience with the flavours adding on to each other.
For dessert, I would say they do a decent and pleasurable job. Sweets are sweets.
Interior wise, also very great. I loved the aesthetic of the place because the usage of the space is genius. Also good color coordination (very nice blend of complimentary colors).
Price wise, you get what you pay for. Do I think the prices are a little high? Yes. Would I continue to pay the prices regardless? Also yes. You cannot substitute quality. I would say it's worth it (also the prices aren't insane this is just a personal review).
Staff and service wise, so welcoming. Lovely staff, they recommend dishes adapt to customers, and greet everyone politely.
The only thing I can nitpick would be the quality of their customer bathrooms. That's it. Everything else is kept in great condition; very clean tables and seating areas.
For someone who is picky and particular in their preferences I would say this establishment will be remembered in a good light for me.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "2 months ago", "authorName": "vickyyy"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "I tried the Dubai cake and tea, and I really enjoyed it. The cake was delicious! The place was very pleasant! It was a clean and beautiful place to eat. I liked the restaurant's interior, the beautiful design, and the comfortable seating arrangements.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "4 weeks ago", "authorName": "Aleksei Plotnikov"}, {"rating": 4, "text": "Took my godfather here for lunch. He hadn‚Äôt had kabob so i was excited for him to try it, he did like his boneless lamb and i got chicken and beef. The ‚Äúhot sauce‚Äù is not so hot it reminded me of a very very mild buffalo sauce, good but not hot/spicy. The rice was also a bit of a let down as it was not authentic saffron rice, they just sprayed/poured over a ‚Äúsaffron like sauce‚Äù definitely not the taste im used to when i hear saffron rice. At the end of the day it was a good experience as the place is designed very modernly.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "4 months ago", "authorName": "Anndy5683"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "My wife said she had a place for us to try for lunch. We pulled into a typical Valley strip mall. Not sure what I was getting into.

We walked into a larger than expected and comfortable dining room. Fortunately the A/C was on and working this August day.

She ordered the gyros plate and I got the gyros wrap with a side of Dolmas.

The food came quickly. I took one bite of my wrapped and immediately was wowed. It was very tasty. The gyros meat was tender and flavorful. I noticed the slices were thinner than normal and I think that is partially why the texture was so good. I remarked that the meat was less greasy than our usual Greek place. The dolmas were just as I like them. Very tasty.

My wife cleaned up her gyros plate.

All in all a good choice.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "2 months ago", "authorName": "Chris Shaul"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "When someone told me that the food was fantastic I was doubtful that it could be THAT good but boy was I wrong.  We went for lunch and they had lunch special which made it even better.   Order at the counter and they bring the food to you.   The protein is made fresh and wow was it super tasty.  I ordered the beef kubideh with rice and two sides.   The hummus was one of my sides and I could just eat this with pita it was so good.   The portion size was very generous and the beef delicious.  Add hot sauce and sumac and it‚Äôs a blast of flavor in each bite.   Staff is very friendly and helpful with any recommendations or explanations of their menu.   Restaurant has many tables and is very clean.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "9 months ago", "authorName": "Katherine Pacpaco"}]

We went here some time last year after a convention to try Ethiopian food for the first time. And omg it was amazing. I'm vegan and have a health condition that effects my digestive system so I sometimes find it difficult to find things that agree with me. The menu has a vegan and vegetarian selection as well as information on some of the different elements of Ethiopian food that people may be unfamiliar with.

My dad is the exact opposite in that he can and will eat anything at least once. He is also very indecisive and will ask the waitress what she suggests. He got a tasting platter with I think 4 different entree items and I got the potatoes and carrots. We both got our entrees with the injeta option. It was absolutely delicious!!! I'm so glad we went there.

I don't go to sac often but when I do, this place is always top of my list to get food. The portions are quite large as it is usually a family style meal (my dad and I couldn't do that bc of my dietary restrictions) and leftovers reheat well.

I got the takeout option this past time and the portion I got will easily be 4 meals for me. I also got the mango drink and as a certified mango lover, I recommend. I've literally been telling all my friends to try Ethiopian food bc it's become one of my go tos.

(The photo is the only one I have from after we finished starting the salad that my dad took bc I can't eat raw veggies)", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a month ago", "authorName": "Alexis Hendrickson"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "I am so very excited. I  made it today for dinner with my daughter.  We both had never been before and were excited to try a new cuisine and enjoy some Ethiopian food.
