reviews:
[{"rating": 5, "text": "The food was great. Service as well. Prices are okay. Our bill was around $35 for the meal in the pictures. It was one shrimp order with broccoli, and order one of their rice that has everything in it. We split between two people. There is parking available. Pleasant atmosphere.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "4 months ago", "authorName": "Fernanda Ayres"}, {"rating": 1, "text": "Our first and last vist yesterday.   Tucked below ground in the basement of an old mill building you won't believe your GPS when it announces "arrived."

Quickly seated our waiter was all smiles as he asked if we wanted drinks,  upon our declining the smile faded.

The menu was more for Japanese food yet the restaurant's name is "Jade"...a gem prized and associated with Chinese.  Their website states, "Where Asian Traditions Meet Modern Elegance In The Heart Of Lowell"

It goes on to mention a fusion, which is accurate...this restaurant is a cross between a sports bar and an Asian restaurant.   The sports bar fills the center of the dining room and as expected appears to be a local watering hole for the Townies.  In addition there is progressive dance music as loud as the conversations.   (Read modern disco)

We were a bit rushed to order, to their credit the appetizers came fast, although not together.   The fried garden roll was typical,  ok.  The seaweed salad,  ok.

After about 10 minutes my wife's dish came, but not mine.   After a long wait and filling up on fried rice and such I walked to the counter to cancel my dish which appeared to be forgotten...at that time the waiter arrived with it and I accepted the late food...a few mins into the dish and he came over to interrupt saying he had warned it was av20 minute dish as it was fried.  No, we were not warned, that was a lie.

Not worth the wait the sesame beef tasted of too much vinegar and over the disco music I imagined hearing,  "what do you want for nothing?   Rrrrrrubbber biscuit??"  The beef was like a Charleston Chew, endless biting to swallow.  I'm not fussy,  I like MREs...this was NOT good food, I don't care who wrote the glowing reviews,  this place sucks.

We got out of there as quickly as possible,  total damage?  $87.54 for two, 15% tip I included out of kindness.   That's $45.00 per head.   There are so many better less expensive restaurants in the area.

The final insult was to demand payment via QR code...which takes you to a website that requires your email address and FORCES you to opt in for marketing 3rd party spam.

My advice?  Ignore the positive reviews here, I have no idea if they are real....trust me, this one is.   Keep walking my brother, sister.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a month ago", "authorName": "Vid Feature"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "Got a large takeout order for a family party. I ordered online. Whole order was correct. Staff helped me out to the car with order.Food was done on time. Everyone loved the food!! Fresh and hot and delicious. We are Chinese food snobs too. We were not disappointed! I highly recommend them!!", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a week ago", "authorName": "Paul DeSisto"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "Jade is fantastic on all levels. Delicious Asian foods. The service is excellent. Energetic atmosphere. Great libations namely the Scorpion bowl's. Dining in or taking out is equally delicious. I enjoy reading all the notes on the wall addressed to Mr. Wong. Support to our communities is evident.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "2 weeks ago", "authorName": "Diane Conlin"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "The menu is creative and well executed the platter for 2 was fresh and flavorful, and the portion sizes were generous. Service was attentive and friendly, and the dining room felt warm and comfortable. Prices were fair for the quality. I‚Äôll definitely be back and recommend Jade to anyone looking for a reliably great Asian-fusion meal in Lowell.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a month ago", "authorName": "Nikki"}]

reviewSummary:
People say this Asian fusion restaurant offers delicious sushi and Chinese food, with generous portions and fresh ingredients. They also highlight the reasonable prices, trendy and clean decor, and attentive service.

Other reviews mention the food can be inconsistent.
reviews:
[{"rating": 5, "text": "I was visiting from outside the country and had a stopover to see my daughter out in Long Island. My daughter took me to Eastern Pavilion after having a great experience here previously and I can see why she recommended it!
The restaurant is very nicely decorated and the staff are very welcoming. We felt right at home. We ordered the pork belly, eggplant, Ocean King roll, Geisha Smile roll, and the Szechuan beef soup. Every dish was very tasty and the portion sizes were very generous, which is perfect for sharing.
Our service was prompt and attentive. Our waiter, the young Wilson, was very friendly and polite. He recommended us some of the best dishes that I have in a long time.
I‚Äôll definitely be coming back the next time I‚Äôm in Long Island.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "4 months ago", "authorName": "Keith Nguyen"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "Today, I had a good time at Eastern Pavilion  and tried the new crispy rice. Everything was amazing. The food and the atmosphere were phenomenal. Wilson, did a really solid job as our server. He was friendly, professional, and made sure everything went smoothly during our visit. He greeted us quickly, got our orders right, and checked in just enough without being too much.

One thing that stood out was how attentive he was ‚Äî refilled our drinks without us having to ask and made sure any special requests were taken care of. You could tell he actually cared about the experience we were having.

Overall, Wilson made the meal more enjoyable with his good attitude and reliable service. Definitely someone you‚Äôd want to have taking care of your table. Would be happy to have him as our server again.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "4 months ago", "authorName": "Michael Jameson"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "We've been regulars at Eastern Pavillion for many years‚Äîfor both take-out and dine-in‚Äîand we've been very happy with the quality and variety of the food. That is especially true after a 2021 fire led to a renovation and expanded menu with a good blend of traditional and asian fusion cuisine...we've tried many of the dishes and have enjoyed them all.

Today, we stopped in for lunch and tried some debut items off their new food and drink happy hour (12-6) menus that the new management (June 2025) introduced. Was too early in the day to try a Japanese Old Fashioned but we tried and loved the new Crispy Rice with Spicy Tuna (and diced jalape√±o on top) small plate and I had some inventive hand rolls with creative ingredients like crispy garlic and truffle cream that added just thr right amount of flavor without being overpowering.

The regular menu items were equally delicious and the service was attentive thanks to Wilson who handled our table.

If you haven't tried EP in a while, may be worth another look. As a Google Guide I consider the negative reviews and most of the ones here predate the 2021 fire and the 2025 new management. I've noticed improvements in recent memory. With so many, many asian food choices in the Three Village area, we would not be repeat customers if the food was not good.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "4 months ago", "authorName": "Kevin Simms"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "Came in for lunch and had an excellent experience at Eastern Pavilion. We ordered a variety of sushi rolls and every single one was outstanding. By far the best sushi I‚Äôve tried in the area! You can tell the fish was incredibly fresh and very generously portioned. You can really taste the difference in ingredients here. I also ordered a martini, which was perfectly made and very tasty with the plum wine.

Shoutout to our waiter Wilson who was very friendly and made sure everything was perfect throughout the meal.

I‚Äôll definitely be returning. Highly recommend!", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "4 months ago", "authorName": "Victoria Nguyen"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "My family and I have been patrons regularly here for over 30 years!  We love their Chinese dishes, always fresh and hot, but we also order Sushi regularly. They always have the freshest high quality fish and ingredients and it's always kept cold unlike some places. They have a large menu and are always willing to make adjustments for the customer as requested.  They also have a bar and hot sake for those who love that.  They did a remodel a few years ago and it has a fresh modern vibe.

We love to dine in but takeout is great too. You can sit at the sushi bar, table or booth and there is a quaint area outside with a waterfall and fishpond. We have sat at the very large round table when we were a big group. We had a graduation party in one of 2 party rooms upstairs and the huge sushi boat that they made was a work of art!  All of the other dishes were loved as well. Parking is never a problem either.

Whoever left that nasty review must be wanting to steer business to another local restaurant.  Every restaurant can have a hiccup on occasion but trust me I'm confident you will enjoy this restaurant run by Mark and his family!!", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "4 months ago", "authorName": "DeEtte Whiteman"}]

generativeSummary: Fresh Asian fusion eatery serving customizable bowls, wraps, noodles, stir-fries and spring rolls alongside fried rice and dumplings.
reviewSummary:
Diners say this Asian fusion restaurant serves up delicious udon noodles with spicy peanut sauce, crispy spring rolls, and potstickers. They also highlight the fast and friendly service, fresh ingredients, and great value for the price.

Some reviews mention the ordering process can be confusing due to the kiosks.
reviews:
[{"rating": 2, "text": "Ordered takeout - two sets of boneless wings (blackberry habanero and buffalo sesame) and some fried rice. When I got home, I thought there must‚Äôve been a mistake - the wings looked totally unsauced. Upon closer examination, it looked like there was a thin layer of sauce on the bottom of each boneless container, so, summoning all of my Saturday Night might, I vigorously shook it and tried to coat the wings the best I could. This is what they looked like afterwards.

Rice was stale and super chewy, and the chicken tasted like microwaved Tyson - not sure if this was a rough night, but this was an awful dinner and a total blowout of 35 bucks.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a week ago", "authorName": "Zachary Brewer"}, {"rating": 4, "text": "I maybe didn't order right, but I didn't get what I wanted and got things I don't like in my noodles. Also, I thought 3 dumplings I ordered were separate not all in the one container. Packaging was good, staff was excellent, and the inside was bright and clean. Intrigued enough to go back again but leary as I keep getting disappointed in takeout food lately.
Update: they add a veggie blend to all stir-fry, so I need to remove that at order. Still, it doesn't explain where the veggies I actually ordered weren't in my meal.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "2 months ago", "authorName": "Hermit Wigglytoes"}, {"rating": 3, "text": "While the atmosphere was fairly decent, I can‚Äôt exactly say the same thing for the food. Otherwise, I will be back.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "8 months ago", "authorName": "MPLSAuntie ‚ÄúMPLSAuntie‚Äù"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "After having a poor experience with someone who wasn't having a great day,  the  manager made it more than 100% right. generativeSummary: Casual, laid-back burger spot serving Cuban-American cuisine like burgers, fries, sandwiches and cocktails.
editorialSummary: Cuban-style burgers & sandwiches are the specialities at this unfussy nook with a relaxed ambiance.
reviewSummary: People say this restaurant serves delicious burgers, Cuban sandwiches, and chop chop salads. They highlight the reasonable prices and relaxed, Miami-inspired vibe. They also like the friendly and attentive staff.
reviews:
[{"rating": 5, "text": "Saw others write about this being the best burger they ever had, and I can attest to that as well. We happened to be there on a night service was great, but the food took a while to arrive. The Vasquez burger was so tender and delicious. It was outstanding. The rest of the food was also good. Value to portion size ratio is okay: not small but not huge. Overall, very good!", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "3 months ago", "authorName": "Jason Murnock"}, {"rating": 2, "text": "First, the good: They had a special side that day of onion rings, and they were excellent. Also the grits were very good. The service was friendly and not bad aside from forgetting a couple of side dishes that we had to ask for twice.

The bad: The food is unimpressive. Both the El Cubano Sandwich and the Crispy Pulled Pork sandwich were dry, and the meat-to-bread ratio was lacking (not enough meat on a thick roll). The Salsa Roja served with the pulled pork was okay, but not zesty enough to flavor a dry, bready sandwich. Better as a dipping sauce. Two of the three who ordered burgers said they didn't taste good. My 11-year-old ate all of his, but the other two adults quit after a bite or two. The Maduros (fried sweet plantains) were chewy; I suspect that either they were made with yellow plantains not ripe enough, or green plantains. The shoestring potatoes served with some dishes are both small in quantity and a waste of time in terms of flavor and edibility. No one ate theirs. I tried one and understood why: they don't taste like anything. I guess we were supposed to add them to the sandwich for crunch, but why? There's already enough starch in the meal.

The ugly: One of our group asked for her burger well done but received a severely undercooked burger. She sent it back. The chef brought out another burger made "smashed" and assured my friend that it was cooked enough. But the inside was raw, even I could see that. My friend again sent it back. She received a complimentary order of grits instead, which were quite nice. But when she got her check, she had been charged for 50% of a burger in addition to her other items. Naturally she complained and they ended up cancelling her check, but the experience didn't make us want to go back. Neither did the food.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "in the last week", "authorName": "DJ Mitchell"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "10/10 would recommend to anyone. Adam was a fantastic server. He was polite, friendly and funny! Not something you get from your every day restaurant. The food was amazing- and took less than 10 minutes to come out! The atmosphere was great as well!", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "7 months ago", "authorName": "Ashley Robey"}, {"rating": 2, "text": "While we've had good experiences with Cuban Burger in the past, this time was different. We received our drinks shortly after coming in and ordered food, which arrived in a normal time. However, after that, we were not checked on in about 30 minutes. We waited and waited and I had to eventually get up and ask for the check. There were two other tables near us with people that got checked on at least last 3 times each and in that time and we were completely ignored when at several points there were many employees just standing around and chatting. I usually tip above 20% but this time they did not earn that. In addition to this the fries I ordered were barely salted and a server never came by so that I could even ask for salt.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a month ago", "authorName": "Gary Winthrope"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "Absolutely amazing. It was pretty dead when we arrived, which is honestly shocking. The fried plantains are some of the best I've ever had stateside. Our server was attentive, and got my mom's weird requests completely right.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "3 weeks ago", "authorName": "Atlas Nosurname"}]

reviewSummary: People say this restaurant serves delicious sesame chicken, chow mein, and orange chicken. They highlight the cozy and casual atmosphere, and the friendly and attentive staff. They also like the generous portions and the lunch specials.
reviews: [{"rating": 1, "text": "I went here to get food because an appointment was delayed. We sat at the table and were informed that we would have to pay a split plate fee.  Even though my daughter wasn‚Äôt eating.  We ordered our food then asked it to go.  They missed the fried rice that we paid for as an upgrade to the white rice.  Food was ok.  The bill was 24 dollars for sweet and sour chicken and two veggie eggrolls.  Overpriced and we didn‚Äôt even get our fried rice.  Not worth the price.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "4 weeks ago", "authorName": "Michael Schreiber"}, {"rating": 2, "text": "8/31/25- First off even though they look like they are closed on the outside with the remodeling going on, they are actually open. There was a smell of saw dust in the air which I like as a former tech kid, but I don't know how others will view the smell. Our server was nice. The problem was the food. I would say it was just average which would have gotten them 3 stars as an average score, but they lost the third star due to the price. Their lunch prices mostly ran $14-17, but in the Denver Metro area there is so much competition for Asian restaurants, and many that have much better food have lunch prices that run $9-12. So they are overpriced for mediocre food. The portions were also smaller then what other places give you for lower prices. Would I go back? Maybe in at least a year to see if they have improved the quality, size, and price of the food. But at present I can not recommend them.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a month ago", "authorName": "Julia Bilderback"}, {"rating": 4, "text": "The pick for a birthday celebration. Not a bad choice for today's outing. Very comfortable and updated atmosphere", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a month ago", "authorName": "Richard Millett"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "Dan is the man! Great location and the food is top tier. I say it's the best Chinese food I've had in Colorado. The place is super clean as well and Dan the owner took great care of us. I highly recommend without hesitation.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "4 months ago", "authorName": "Francisco Colin"}]

generativeSummary: Relaxed restaurant serving Italian classics, including subs, pasta, and pizza, plus beer.
reviews:
[{"rating": 4, "text": "Nice place in a strip mall. The building looks newer from the outside, inside shows it‚Äôs age, but clean and well lit. Not a big place but I like that. I had a meatball sub, add jalape√±os and it came with fries. My wife had the manicotti. The food came pretty quickly and was hot. First thing I noticed was my jalape√±os were not on my sub. Then I flashed back to when I asked for them, the waitress didn‚Äôt know if they had jalape√±os or not. I looked at the menu for pizza topping and they were there. When she returned for our first taste check in I pointed out my jalape√±o dilemma. She apologized and went to get them. She returned with hot banana peppers. I ate those, I was too hungry. The sub was good, a little more marinara would have good but not bad. The fries were crisp, hot, and not greasy. My wife enjoyed the manicotti but the large portion made her ask for a doggie bag. When the check came. There was a service fee, 3.99%, $1.00, added to the ticket. I‚Äôve seen service fees charged for credit cards, so I thought that was it. I asked and the waitress had no idea what it‚Äôs for but explained she had nothing to do with it and couldn‚Äôt take it off. Never heard of such a thing. I would still like to know. Everything was good and I will be back. The waitress was very good but maybe new to the industry. I will return and try an entree on that trip. Still would like an answer on the service fee.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "2 months ago", "authorName": "Jack Mace"}, {"rating": 2, "text": "I love their pizza. It's consistently great. But their "italian" hoagie is inedible. It's 2 slices of ham, tiny bit of provolone, and 1 measly, pale slice of capicola. A bunch of lettuce, way too much mayo, no oil and vinegar, no seasoning. It comes toasted. I was hungry so I was going to eat it anyway, but it's literally bad. I took one bite and threw it out. Wawa does a better Italian hoagie than this. You cannot call yourself an Italian restaurant with this bad of an Italian hoagie.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "3 months ago", "authorName": "Nicole Morris-Anastasi"}, {"rating": 3, "text": "Read the reviews and then ordered online. It didn‚Äôt say anything about french fries coming with the sub but when you scroll through all the extra toppings and additions and subtractions, it said if you didn‚Äôt want fries, you could get chips at no charge however they delivered my sub there are no french fries so I paid extra for a sub with no fries. I could‚Äôve driven the six minutes to the restaurant and I would‚Äôve got fries and it would‚Äôve been cheaper because the delivery menu is more expensive than the regular menu. It‚Äôs all very confusing but if you order online, you don‚Äôt get the same stuff that you get in the restaurant the Delivery was greatDelivery is fast and easy.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "in the last week", "authorName": "Casey Boxall"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "Dined in today with my daughter and felt like we got special treatment. It was a late lunch on a Saturday and it wasn‚Äôt busy. Waiter/chef was attentive and gave great recommendations. We had a Principessa pizza and some pasta. Magnificent! Not even a bite of crust was wasted! Thank you for not disappointing. I recommend for friendly people that enjoy small restaurants.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "3 years ago", "authorName": "Preston Burns"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "This place is the real deal!! Fresh, high quality ingredients. Crust made from scratch. You will not regret spending a few extra dollars on this pizza compared to other spots.

We ordered the garlic knots and principessa pizza and picked it up early.

The dough is clearly made fresh in house with a nice taste and delightful texture. High quality toppings included fresh spinach and mushrooms sauteed in olive oil. Sausage is uniquely sliced and delicious without being too heavy.

Real, tasty olive oil on the garlic knots with fresh garlic and lots of oregano.

We've gotten Arianna's twice now and the quality will continue to bring us back. Everything is made of fresh, real food. Too often I order a cheap pizza that tastes like fake preservatives and chemicals, I dont know why I ever do that to myself when Arianna's is right here! As of this review I'm just not gonna waste my time with any other pizza. Arianna's, I will return soon!!", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "3 years ago", "authorName": "Chelsea Branson"}]

reviews:
[{"rating": 4, "text": "Took the family to Brooklyn's Pizzaria. Had wonderful service from the staff! Very attentive, friendly, and gave suggestions. Greeted with a smile, sat quickly, no wait. Atmosphere was obviously Brooklyn, NY related. Cozy, Hometown, homegrown feel. Clean and nicely done.
Food was delicious. Most items had great taste and full of flavor. The white pizza looked like it would have been dry but it was amazing. The pepperoni pizza had great flavor. Calzone was perfectly cooked, great amount of ricotta and pepperoni. The garlic knots were ok. Not a ton of flavor on these guys. We'll pass on the knots next time. But we will be back for more. Give them a shout. We'll see you there.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a month ago", "authorName": "Kristopher Sargeant"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "Excellent communication, friendly service and good food.
We have ordered multiple times and even got the pizzas for my son's graduation party last month, and the food is always good.

But I wanted to share about last night.

I preordered 4 meals online for take-out and was given an estimated time, but since it was peak hours (Friday night) they were a bit busy but communicated within less than a minute that it would take 7 minutes longer than estimated. When my husband came in (the original time) to pick it up and it wasn't ready (which we already knew because of the great communication) he ordered a beer while he waited, and they said "no charge" because of the wait. My husband was so surprised and happy and when he came home, he couldn't stop talking about how nice they were to him.

Brooklyn's Pizzeria will definitely keep being a go-to for us.

Thanks for the kindness and excellent service.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a month ago", "authorName": "Annika Weaver"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "I was on my way to Orlando from Jacksonville and came across this little gem.  The wife and I ordered a side of meatballs and a Margherita pizza.  My Italian wife is a meatball snob since no one can make one like her grandmother.  But when she said they were damn close that is as strong a praise as she will ever provide.  We actually had to order a second round since we devoured them before I remembered to take a photo.  The pizza was awesome.  For me personally, i judge a Philly cheesesteak by the roll and I judge a pizza by the crust.  The crust was on the thinner side which I prefer but had a perfect amount of chew and was moist and flavorful.  The sauce which I was told they made fresh was seasoned perfectly with a bold fresh tomato taste.  The sauce reminded me of this pie I ate on my honeymoon in Venice.  Now I can just travel to Leesburg and get a fantastic pie and can let my passport expire.  I really wish I could remember our servers name because she deserves to be called out by name.  Everything you could want, attentive but not to the point she was interrupting our time together.  Restaurant and bathrooms were cleaned and that was obviously a focus of theirs which is unfortunately rare these days.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "8 months ago", "authorName": "Douglas Williams"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "I walked into my favorite Italian pie store today after finding out it is under new ownership. It is about an hour from where I live, so I don't get it often. Emma was glad to see me, and Nick made my pie as wonderful as he has been making them for at least 5 years. I also met Jordan, the manager, who is dedicated to keeping the great quality of the food here.  Definitely worth the drive.  Thank you all for a great meal and a wonderful experience! phil", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a month ago", "authorName": "Phillip Stoes"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "Michell was excellent server. She checked on my table making sure we did not need anything. She was attentive to our needs.. my calzone was excellent. Thank you Michell for the great service. We will definitely be back", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "5 months ago", "authorName": "Darlene Latham"}]

generativeSummary: Casual restaurant specializing in shwarmas (sandwiches) and falafel, as well as catering and takeout.
reviewSummary: People say this Middle Eastern restaurant serves delicious beef and chicken shawarma, falafel, and kafta. They highlight the fresh ingredients, homemade food, and generous portions, as well as the reasonable prices and fast service. They also like the friendly staff, welcoming atmosphere, and the management's hospitality.
reviews:
[{"rating": 5, "text": "I have had their delicious food multiple times now with nothing but praise for the taste and their customer service.

Things happen sometimes and last night I ordered takeout stopping on my way home from work.

I took my food and didn‚Äôt realize until I got home that the order was wrong and I was missing a few items.

Here is where I stress again, things happen.  I was hungry and was upset for a quick minute and then took a breath and realized it was on me too for not checking the order before leaving.  Also, instead of immediately leaving an angry review, I wanted to go back and give them a chance.

Well they certainly delivered!  Of course they let me keep what I did get (ate it for lunch today), cooked me the correct meal, and gave me a free piece of delish dessert.

While waiting for the food I had a nice conversation with some of the staff and they all were nice and sincerely apologetic.

That, right there, is how things should be handled by both parties.  I really appreciate them taking care of me and once again, they earned my respect and repeat business.

See you all soon!  Thank you for being part of the Olmsted small business family!", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "3 weeks ago", "authorName": "Jeff"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "AMAZING service! Reham was sooo sweet, friendly, and kind to my son and I when we came in. Because of her wonderful service, we will absolutely be back soon! She also made the Habibi fries and they were delicious!", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "3 weeks ago", "authorName": "Taylor Lehmann"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "Yalla Shawarma in North Olmsted serves flavorful Middle Eastern dishes in a clean, modern setting. The chicken shawarma is juicy and well-seasoned, pairing perfectly with their creamy garlic sauce. Habibi Fries are a must-try‚Äîcrispy, loaded, and delicious. Hummus and lentil soup also shine. While service is often friendly, some reviews note inconsistent quality, especially with beef dishes. Overall, a great spot for fresh, satisfying shawarma‚Äîstick to the chicken for the best experience.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "2 months ago", "authorName": "Eli"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "I recently had the pleasure of trying the chicken and beef shawarma with fries, Habibi style, for the first time, and I was absolutely blown away! The shawarma was incredibly flavorful, and the fries complemented it perfectly. What made it even better was the array of sauces that came with the dish ‚Äì each one had its own unique taste, making it so much fun to dip and savor.

The dessert was also a treat, and the overall experience was made even better by the exceptional service. From the warm welcome to the attentive service while taking our order, the staff made sure we felt taken care of every step of the way. It‚Äôs rare to find such a high level of hospitality.

I can‚Äôt wait to go back and try the mixed grill next time. I highly recommend this place to anyone looking for great food and an unforgettable dining experience!", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "6 months ago", "authorName": "Ala Alqasem"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "This restaurant is amazing. The staff was so nice and the food was flavorful and filling. Great price and perfect menu. Very fast service as well. You should definitely check it out! I got the falafel wrap and veggie kafta. Both were amazing!", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "3 months ago", "authorName": "okaytyga"}]

reviewSummary: People say this ramen restaurant serves delicious shio and miso ramen with deep, savory broth and perfectly cooked, elastic noodles. reviews:
[{"rating": 5, "text": "This location opened a mere month ago (Sept. 30th, I think) and i can already see it becoming a favorite. The food was, as always, amazing. I lived a block away from the Costa Mesa location for around 3 years. The Tsukemen (dipping noodles) with shouyu broth was excellent. The service was top-tier. I forgot to get the server's name but she was an Indonesian/South East Asian lady with a pleasant attitude and glad to be helping us. The ambiance is also incredible. And the food? It's straight out of Japan. The broth is deep and savory, and the noodles are perfectly cooked‚Äînice and elastic with a satisfying bite. reviews:
[{"rating": 5, "text": "This was our first time here. My daughter and I came about 430ish pm. I noticed the guy in front of me wanted to order a meal but the meat wouldn't be ready for at least 40 mins, he tried to change it up to get something fast but the meal he wanted wouldn't be ready until at least 530pm. I was surprised, it seems like a quick order place but thought maybe because it was the time of day? Not sure.
We ordered 2 orders of cheese fries, 2 fountain drinks, and 2 Dubai strawberry chocolate (the strawberries were the real reason we came). The person who took our order was patient and nice. What we ordered was $50.
We ate in the restaurant. It was clean and cute.
The fountain drinks were not it, weird to say but they tasted awful. They have the same drinks as Sugar Fire ans those taste great but their ratio must be off or something here. Its drinks so no reason to complain but order a different drink other than the fountain drinks. The fries came and not what we were expecting, they were drenched in the cheese sauce. The cheese sauce had a good flavor but why they put so much on was disappointing. The fries were soggy and inedible. The Dubai chocolate strawberries were great.
I will definitely give this restaurant another try but will know if you want meat dishes you better order ahead, don't order the fountain drinks, definitely dont order the cheese fries, the dessert was so good.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a month ago", "authorName": "Jami Struthers"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "I try a lot of Mediterranean cuisine all around St. Louis and this one is one of my top favorites. On top of that, they included a warm pack of soft pita bread, perfect for dipping ‚Äî such a thoughtful touch that really elevated the meal. The takeout ordering process was quick and easy, the staff was friendly and helpful, and my order was ready right on time.

If you‚Äôre looking for fresh Mediterranean takeout or catering, or just craving the best hummus and pita around, I highly recommend checking out Golden Chicken. reviews:
[{"rating": 5, "text": "‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è‚≠êÔ∏è

Efi‚Äôs is the best authentic Greek & Mediterranean cuisine in New Jersey‚Äîhands down.
Their menu hits every note: gyros, souvlaki, falafel, salads, and housemade dips that deliver bold, fresh flavor.

‚Ä¢ Signature dishes: Chicken gyro, beef & lamb gyro, grilled lamb souvlaki, and build-your-own bowls
‚Ä¢ Quality ingredients: USDA-inspected meats, fresh produce, and imported Greek staples like feta, olive oil, and pita
‚Ä¢ Clean cooking: No gluten, MSG, preservatives, or antibiotics in their meats

Efi‚Äôs deserves recognition for making THE BEST TZATZIKI in North America, never mind New Jersey. This establishment deserves a Michelin Bib Gourmand award for their exceptional food and service. The staff is welcoming, and genuinely committed to making every visit memorable.

As for the owner, Stephano‚Äîhis commitment to customer service blew me away. I placed a late dinner order and ran to CVS before it arrived. When I got home, I found two full orders. I hadn‚Äôt been charged twice, so I called to clarify. Stephano explained he was worried about the Uber driver‚Äôs timing and personally sent a second order with his own driver to ensure I‚Äôd be taken care of. That‚Äôs not just good service‚Äîit‚Äôs elite.

Whether you‚Äôre grabbing lunch or catering for a crowd, Efi‚Äôs delivers Michelin-grade hospitality and flavor. I imagine Heaven being an all you can eat buffet with Efi‚Äôs catering and never ending supply of Efis homemade tzatziki.

Efis isn‚Äôt just a gyro shop‚Äîit‚Äôs a taste of home and heaven.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "2 weeks ago", "authorName": "Jacob Lombardi"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "Came in here because I was hungry and I saw a sign. Great decision. It was delicious.

There are a lot of options but I decided to go : Efi's Gyro. Beware, Efi's sauce is spicy but has so much flavor! The fries, that were in the gyro but I had to eat separately, were seasoned and crispy. I definitely want to try the rest of the menu but at least I have a safe go-to!
A lot of seating was also available.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "5 months ago", "authorName": "KrisKat Meow"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "The best gyro ever! The meat is incredibly juicy and tender, and some of the best fries I‚Äôve ever had. Every bite is packed with flavor. On top of that, the owner is super nice and welcoming, which makes the whole experience even better. You can really feel how much pride they take in their food and service. Highly recommend to anyone who loves great gyros because this is my go to spot several times a week!", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "in the last week", "authorName": "Inri Panajoti"}, {"rating": 4, "text": "Stopped by Elfi‚Äôs recently, and I‚Äôve got to say‚Äîit‚Äôs a really lovely spot. The space is clean, nicely decorated, and has a warm, welcoming vibe that makes you want to stay a little longer.

What stood out most, though, was the staff. Everyone was super friendly and genuinely kind. You can tell they care about the place and the people who come in. That kind of hospitality makes a big difference.

The food? Solid. The presentation is clean and thoughtful, and the quality‚Äôs definitely there. It‚Äôs not over-the-top fancy, but it doesn‚Äôt need to be‚Äîit‚Äôs good, and it‚Äôs made with care.

If I had to nitpick, I‚Äôd say the portion sizes could be a bit more generous. Nothing major, just something that would make the overall experience even better.

All in all, Elfi‚Äôs is the kind of local business that deserves more love. Good food, great people, and a place that feels like part of the community. I‚Äôll definitely be back.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "6 months ago", "authorName": "Massimo"}, {"rating": 4, "text": "Overall food quality was good. We ordered a beef platter. Service was fast and staff were friendly. There is plenty of seating indoor and out. The meat although tasty is slightly salty. Fries are crispy and delicious. Prices are moderate.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "3 months ago", "authorName": "Jonathan Lim"}]

generativeSummary: Casual eatery featuring a variety of Himalayan specialties such as lentil soup and beef curry, as well as dumplings.
editorialSummary: Warm, wood-paneled restaurant with traditional decor serving Tibetan dishes such as momo & pingsha.
reviewSummary: People say this Tibetan restaurant serves delicious momo dumplings, flavorful soups, and fresh vegetables. They highlight the unique and authentic flavors, and the wide variety of vegetarian options. They also like the friendly and attentive service.
reviews: [{"rating": 5, "text": "Delicious food! I‚Äôd definitely come here again. I got the mutton curry as my main dish, which was fantastic, but really everything was great. I would be happy to come here again and try out more things on the menu!\nMy only issue with this place is that you can hear people‚Äôs conversations very easily, which you can hear in the video. If they had a way to insulate the sound a bit so it doesn‚Äôt reverberate off the walls and travel so easily, I think it could help. Otherwise a wonderful placeüòä", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a month ago", "authorName": "Rebecca Cooper"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "White yak is a Tibetan restaurant in roxborough, first of its kind in Philly! I really enjoyed the variety of Tibetan food here. We started with mung bean jelly (cold noodle dish) which is super refreshing, 5/5. Then my partner and I shared the combo Momo which includes 3 beef momos, 3 chicken momos and 3 vegetarian momos. The flavors were all different, letting customers to be able to try the vast world of Tibetan/nepalese dumplings. We also ordered thenthuk, hand pulled noodle soup, which is very warming and perfect to have on the rainy day we visited. We washed all of this down with a traditional butter tea, slightly savory with creaminess. The waiter was super friendly. We were able to chat about our individual experiences in Tibet. We would come back again!", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "2 weeks ago", "authorName": "Keeks"}, {"rating": 4, "text": "stumbled upon this restaurant and saw many locals eating inside so decided to give it a try. we were happy we did. we enjoyed everything we ate. menu highlights: himalayan momos and the chicken curry with the baos for dipping (fun and yummy).", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "2 weeks ago", "authorName": "Lori Lam"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "Yes, a new fav! 2nd time ordering from here and everything was flavorful. The lentil soup was hearty with levity and loved the bits of ginger at the bottom of the soup container. The Thenthuk broth cured something in my soul and noodles was the perfect amount of thickness and chewy softness. The beef is more lean than what I would like so I stick with the veggie Thenthuk. The Chili Momo sauce has a kick and builds the more you eat it. I prefer the meat dumplings over the veggies bc the thick dough does a good job soaking up the flavor. The texture of the eggplant in the Gha is more cooked than what I would like but the balance of savory and tangy garlic is wonderful. The steam buns go well dipped in the curry sauce of the Pingsha. Will order again.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a week ago", "authorName": "Quynh-Mai Nguyen"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "This is one of Philadelphia‚Äôs ELITE gems. BYO and phenomenal food. Every single shred of vegetable is hand washed by the owner and everything is made with the upmost care and love. The food is elite but the people who own and also run this place are even better. We wouldn‚Äôt be the same city without them and that‚Äôs not even up for debate. We eat here weeekly lol. HIGHLY recommend.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "2 weeks ago", "authorName": "Pancakes and Protein Shakes"}]

Oysters tasted wierd and not fresh (this may be because we normally get them at Miller's in galveston where they taste like they are right outta the ocean)  I did enjoy the atmosphere because it looks authentically like a great seafood house. When we initially walked in the waitress was in a back office on her cell phone and did not initially greet us. I feel that she finished her text and then came out to tell us how to order and then disappeared back into the office. She did re-emerge to take our order with a little lack luster. We were specifically hesitant to eat here because of the comments about the platinum haired waitress (which is who we got) I ended up tipping her 20% to bring food to the table to never be seen again.  Then it was like my girl bothered her asking for a to go bag after having to get our own to go boxes because we were never checked on again after she brought our food.  Maybe she was having a bad day but this is how places go outta business and I am obviously not the first to have an issue with the lack of hospitality. I had a variety off apps (humus, dolmas, and spanokopita).  I was very pleasantly surprised.  The dolmas were well balanced, spiced well,  and firm.  The humus had a great taste and the pita was fresh and very fluffy,  it was not thin pita.   The spanikopita was fresh and made recently but was very not traditional, I would get again though.

Pleasant place and nice atmosphere,  I was there for lunch and it was fairly full.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "in the last week", "authorName": "Eric Heppen"}, {"rating": 1, "text": "Ordered a lamb gyro and got shredded tough lamb (not gyro)in a hard pita , old fries that were also hard. For other first timers: you go in and order at a counter, they'll give you your cups and then you pick a table and they'll call your name when your food is ready. They have the menu on the wall but also hand held sheets so you can stand to the side and make up your mind. The food was good, the men making the plates were friendly and you get plenty for your money (I ate twice from my portion). Our only small issue was that the lady that took our order didn't want the experienced person to order lamb. Maybe they were out or running low, but he gave his order and she kept repeating a version of: pork is our traditional meat, pork is the traditional order, etc , and by the third time she said it, he gave in and ordered the pork, then during the meal he said that having had them both now, he should have insisted on the lamb. reviews:
[{"rating": 5, "text": "We came to celebrate our 6th wedding anniversary. Our server Molly was very informative and her recommendations were SPOT on. The food was unbelievable. We started with the charred octopus and it was phenomenal, the sauce, the texture, and the accoutrements were perfect. We took Mollys recommendation and got the rack of lamb as one of our entrees and it was hands down one of the best we‚Äôve ever tried. The desserts are chefs kiss!! So tasty. The restaurant is super clean, the staff is super friendly, we will definitely be coming back. Thank you!", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "2 weeks ago", "authorName": "Olivia McElhenney"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "An Unforgettable Culinary Experience

From start to finish, Myrtoe delivered one of the best dining experiences I‚Äôve had in a long time. The ambiance was warm and inviting, and every dish we tried was bursting with flavor and authenticity.

We started with the octopus and falafel, both of which were exceptional. The octopus was perfectly tender with a charred finish that added depth, while the falafel was crispy on the outside, fluffy on the inside, and beautifully seasoned.

For our mains, we had the chicken kabab and the rack of lamb ‚Äî and wow. The chicken was juicy, marinated to perfection, and grilled just right. The lamb was tender, rich, and cooked flawlessly, with every bite melting in our mouths.

We couldn‚Äôt resist dessert and were so glad we didn‚Äôt. The baklava was flaky and sweet with just the right amount of spice, and the ek-mek kataife was a revelation ‚Äî creamy, crunchy, and not too heavy, the perfect ending to our meal.

To top it all off, our server Lisa was absolutely amazing. Attentive, kind, knowledgeable, and genuinely passionate about the food and our experience ‚Äî she made the evening even more memorable.

If you‚Äôre looking for a spot that blends heartwarming hospitality with truly exceptional Greek cuisine, Myrtoe is it. Can‚Äôt wait to come back!", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "4 months ago", "authorName": "Matt Indelicato"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "One of the best restaurants in Chester County! I‚Äôve been here several times and I‚Äôve yet to have a bad meal. Everything is always fresh and so delicious! Great food, atmosphere, and customer service

reviewSummary: People say this restaurant serves authentic Nepali and Indian dishes, including momos, curries, and thali. They highlight the fresh ingredients, flavorful and comforting food, and the cozy and welcoming vibe. They also like the friendly and attentive staff.
reviews:
[{"rating": 5, "text": "This is the best place for all the heavy hitters.  I am so thrilled with the level of culinary skill that I want everyone who appreciates great desi food to get to experience the food here.  I started coming here a month after they opened. I've probably eaten here 5 times and ordered out 4 times.

In particular, these are my favorite things to order:

The Non-Veg platter.  It includes:
------
Tandoori Chicken:  most tender tandoori chicken I've ever had in ages.  It compared a legendary tandoori spot that I went to in the Margalla Hills in Pakistan.

Chicken Manchurian:  a classic indochinese fusion dish, it takes crispy fried chicken and tosses it in a perfectly tangy, not too spicy, savory sauce.

Chili Momo (4 pieces):  The crispy fried dumpling is filled with a juicy, herbaceous, super tasty ground chicken. It's then tossed In sauce of garlicy onions & bell peppers.

Fried fish:  perfectly fried appetizer bites of breaded fish are topped with minced fried red onions. The topping is SO GOOD.
------

Butter Chicken: you can taste the Ghee and the cream. It's so good and the chicken is tender tender tender.   It's served with fluffy basmati rice in copper dishes.

Chicken Lababdar. A Mughlai dish that you never see on most menus unless you're in South Asia. This is a MUST try. The chicken is tender and the cashew, ghee, and cream sauce is incredible. We always order this.

Naan:  The fluffy garlic naan is topped with ghee and there is whole fennel seed in the dough.  It tastes so good when it's cooked.

Chapati- 2 smaller pieces in an order. They are soft and delicious.

Gulab Jamun- served warm. It is THE BEST  with layers of flavor, made with ghee, bathed in an aromatic syrup.

Mango lassi- they use fresh mango. It's great.

All the chutneys and sauces are substantial, super fresh, and aromatic.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a month ago", "authorName": "Faeza ‚ÄúSacredKnowledge‚Äù Moghul"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "Amazing food.  I'm gonna be a regular at this place. The ambiance was excellent and pleasant. It's pretty good smelling. All the dishes were delicious. Worth trying it.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "3 months ago", "authorName": "Siddhartha Konapala"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "The food was delicious here, I highly recommend the alloo samosas, butter chicken and thali meal plates! I was craving Indian food and this place certainly hits the spot. Will be back for more!", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a month ago", "authorName": "Kathy Lee"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "Super cozy and pretty place in the middle of sf. The food is actually SO good and the prices are so fair?? Best Nepalese restaurant in the bay hands down.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "3 months ago", "authorName": "Xiaolin Liu"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "Fabulous food, generous wine pour! GOAT biryani,tandoori chicken salad, and fish kabobs! Delicious üíú", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "2 months ago", "authorName": "lisa lloyd"}]

generativeSummary: Cozy spot for tacos and other Mexican eats, plus margaritas (including frozen).
reviewSummary: People say this restaurant serves delicious ceviche, chimichangas, and plantains. They highlight the authentic Mexican cuisine, tasty margaritas, and generous portions. They also like the friendly staff and quick service.
reviews:
[{"rating": 3, "text": "The Food:
We ordered the Made to Order Guacamole, Ceviche, and 6 street tacos (2 sets of 3, 1 set not pictured). I personally tried the ground beef and Tinga chicken street tacos, the Made to Order Guacamole, and a small bite of the Ceviche. My favorite part of the meal was the fresh guacamole. Not only could you tell it was fresh, but it was very well portioned and was more than enough for two people. We had no problems adding some to our tacos but still having some for the chips. I was largely unsatisfied by the tacos. The flavor of the tortilla overpowered everything else. The Tinga Chicken had virtually no flavor other than the tortilla, and although I could taste the ground beef, I couldn‚Äôt help but think I could make better at home with some taco bell seasoning. I think the tacos would significantly improve with less tortilla (or maybe fuse them together so there‚Äôs not so much in every bite?). I used the green sauce on my tacos and it was very delicious - so much so that I was able to finish the meal with minimal issues despite aforementioned complaints. If I order tacos, I don‚Äôt expect the sauce to carry the flavor. The ceviche was okay. It was cooked and tasted as described so I think it is only personal preference that I didn‚Äôt enjoy it.

The Service:
Our server was kind and spoke slowly. This helped us not miss anything he was saying but I couldn‚Äôt help but wonder if he was tired, which would be understandable because we came right before closing. He was helpful in selecting from the menu, and our food came out promptly and just as we ordered.

The Atmosphere:
It was a nice setup, I enjoyed sitting at the high top tables which included a booth and a high seat. The music was a good volume, it was just loud enough that you couldn‚Äôt hear other tables but not too loud where you couldn‚Äôt hear the person you were sharing a meal with. We noticed to at one of the TV‚Äôs was casting from someone‚Äôs personal youtube and showed an execution from another country‚Äôs news channel. That was wild, unexpected, and not something we would have expected of this establishment. It would be much appreciated if the media shared was more closely monitored.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "2 weeks ago", "authorName": "Aleena Milburn"}, {"rating": 4, "text": "This place is owned by the owners of El Sabor I believe, and I really enjoyed El Sabor, so I decided to give this spot a try. Wow. It did not disappoint! Wayyy better than Chipotle. I got to try their BYO bowl with yellow rice, cheese, yucca bites, sweet plantains, and sweet and spicy chipotle sauce. I also threw in one of their tres leches cake slices.

Everything was pretty much perfect, even without a protein! The yucca was perfectly fried and so sweet and flavorful. The yucca was also great and went perfectly with that very balanced, delicious sauce. Even the rice was great! I will say the cheese is a bit rubbery.

The tres leches was also amazing. Solid portion, perfect amount of sweetness, drenched in that delicious milk. Very nice.

All in all, I highly recommend both this place and El Sabor for the fresh and delicious food they make.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a month ago", "authorName": "Ulyana K"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "Came here with a friend for some margaritas and dinner and had a great time. The ceviche and shrimp quesadilla were both absolutely delicious! I also greatly enjoyed the margaritas and loved that I could get mine rimmed with tajin instead of salt. Great experience overall and will definitely be back.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "6 months ago", "authorName": "April Roberson"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "Absolutely delicious, highly recommend the green beans and plantains! We will definitely return when the weather is nicer. You might want a reservation though as this is a smaller venue and we almost didn‚Äôt get a seat as a walk-in.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "5 months ago", "authorName": "Dorothy Ingram"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "Fresh food, filling portions, friendly staff.  Everything was delicious! We ate in-house with a to go order added on, and both were very nice experiences. Of course, dining in is the best. The waiter was attentive and available.  The inside was clean and well organized. Looking forward to returning for more styles of salsas and tacos!", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a year ago", "authorName": "Christopher Field"}]

reviews:
[{"rating": 4, "text": "I recently visited Madurai Kitchen and Bar as I had cravings for a good vegetarian meal and decided to give their veg meals a try. Unfortunately, the experience wasn‚Äôt quite what I expected. The veg meals turned out to be authentic South Indian style, specifically in the Tamil Nadu tradition, which might be great for people who are used to and love that regional flavor. However, for me, the taste was a bit disappointing and didn‚Äôt match what I was hoping for.

On the positive side, the quantity was generous and definitely filling, so it felt worth the $20 in terms of portion size. Still, the flavors just didn‚Äôt stand out or feel satisfying enough for the price. Since I only tried the veg meals, I can‚Äôt comment on the other dishes on the menu‚Äîmaybe they have better options‚Äîbut based on this experience, I left a little unsatisfied.

Overall, I‚Äôd say the place might be a good fit for someone specifically looking for authentic Tamil Nadu‚Äìstyle South Indian meals, but if you‚Äôre looking for a broader or more balanced vegetarian experience, the taste might not fully meet expectations.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a month ago", "authorName": "NagaSai Chowdary"}, {"rating": 3, "text": "Food look nice but taste mediocre for expensive price and don‚Äôt know add on prices in bill. Baby corn manchurian was good.

Gobi Manchurian:  below average

reviewSummary: People say this Chinese restaurant serves flavorful dumplings, noodles, and spicy beef soup. They highlight the fast service, convenient mobile ordering system, and authentic Sichuan-style dishes. They also like the cozy ambiance and attentive service.
reviews:
[{"rating": 5, "text": "The flavor of every dish is absolutely incredible. Waiter was good about refilling water. I enjoy ordering and paying via my phone as it gives me more control of my own time. The waiter packed up all of our leftovers for us when we were done. easy 5 stars", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a week ago", "authorName": "Josh Pickles"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "Pretty good, everything was very flavorful and came out super hot. You order on your food and order goes directly to kitchen and comes out really fast. Good for in between classes. The spicy beef soup was very good as well as the dumplings", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a month ago", "authorName": "Emma"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "Delicious SiChuan Chinese food. It‚Äôs a theme restaurant about the history of Chengdu. The dolls from SanXingDui are adorable! I like the atmosphere and the house decorating. It deserves a try!", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "2 months ago", "authorName": "Yaru Xue"}, {"rating": 3, "text": "I ordered from Damao many times, even the one in Chinatown before they changed to catering only. Well over 20 times.

Food is one of a kind for chicago. Not many places where you will find Chengdu food. I mostly get the Hotpot with veggies / meats.

Food can be very inconsistent. For the most part (75-80%) it is good. But sometimes when I order the same items as I did last week, the taste is off. Sometimes, it is not salty enough and very bland and I can only taste the oil. There was 2 times where there was so much pepper corn in the soup, I was literally eating pepper corns with a side of vegetables.

Nonetheless,  still a fan of this place. I hope they improve the consistency of their food. When and if they do, this review will change to 5 stars.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "3 weeks ago", "authorName": "Jack Yu"}, {"rating": 3, "text": "I was really looking forward to trying Royal Highness Zhu. I will say that the food was alright. It seemed like some of the dishes like the vegetable hot pot was not cooked all the way through and the sizzle sausage fried rice did not have any sausage in it. That is really disappointing. I will say the best dish I had was the zhong dumplings. The taste was really on point. I did make a reservation and the male server/ host was really rude and did not accept my reservation. That same male server told me that he was too busy too for a few requests we had. I am not sure if it was me but, he just seemed very rude. I will say the ambiance or atmosphere was really nice. I will say give royal highness zhu a chance and for sure ask someone how to order as the menu system was kind of strange to me.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a year ago", "authorName": "Chicago Bae Reviews"}]

[{"rating": 4, "text": "Formerly was flame broiler, but that's no more!
For a quick bite during lunch I recommend getting a bowl. You get one protein and two sides. Tru the spicy chicken with kimchi and white rice. They have some of the absolute best kimchi I have ever had, I am not joking or exaggerating. Their ingredients are extremely fresh and there is no sour taste in anything. If you're feeling a bit more hungry then I suggest you try their big plate. Parking: street parking is terrible as this is across from the court house, HOWEVER there is a parking structure you can park in. Two entrances to the structure: one on broadway and one on 3rd Street, please account for this. If you haven't gave this spot a try, please do. Please try the kimchi!!", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a week ago", "authorName": "Aracely Esparza"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "Great selection of favorite entrees and sides! generativeSummary: Casual eatery offering Cuban fare such as mofongo, sandwiches, and flan, plus BYOB.
editorialSummary: Colorful, unassuming strip-mall cafe with a menu of Cuban & Puerto Rican favorites.
reviewSummary:
People say this Cuban restaurant serves delicious Cuban sandwiches, yucca, and plantains. They also highlight the affordable prices, cozy atmosphere, and friendly service.

Other reviews mention the food can be inconsistent.
reviews:
[{"rating": 5, "text": "9/10 The ambiance was set perfectly with pictures, paintings, and other  Cuban elements. The food was delicious and was brought out very quickly, despite the restaurant being full of guests. The host was friendly, informative, and set a welcoming tone.  We ordered the Cubano, which was perfectly balanced with the ideal amounts of each signature ingredient, Yucca Frita, which was carefully finished with flaky salt, Tostones Rellenos, which were served in a pair and the plantain cups were delicately flaky and carrying a rather large serving of tender delicious brisket, Guandules (yellow rice) which was cooked with pigeon peas and sofrito which gave it much more flavor than plain rice. I would reccomended all of the dishes, but the Cubano and the Tostones Rellenos stood out for sure. I doubt you could go wrong ordering anything here, though! We will definitely be back to try more dishes and leave room for desserts next time.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "3 months ago", "authorName": "Bennett Smith (Umami Haven)"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê‚≠ê

I recently dined at The Latin Pig, Cuban Cuisine,  and it was an incredible experience that transported me straight to Cuba!

For starters, the Arroz Congri was perfectly seasoned, combining black beans and rice in a delightful harmony of flavors. The Arroz con Gandules was equally impressive, bursting with the rich, savory taste of pigeon peas that paired wonderfully with the tender rice.

The main dishes were the stars of the show! The Ropa Vieja was stunning‚Äîslow-cooked beef with vibrant spices that practically melted in my mouth. The Picadillo offered a comforting blend of ground beef, olives, and spices.

The Fried Plantain just how it‚Äôs supposed to be cooked, and for the sweet tooth the Coconut Flan and Vanilla Flan, creamy and sweet!

And to top it off, the service, warm and welcoming! I could‚Äôve given 50 stars if I could!!!", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "5 months ago", "authorName": "Ximena Silva"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "If you want delicious Cuban food, for amazing prices and fantastic service - this is the place. It makes sure I don‚Äôt miss my Miami Cuban food it is that good. 10000% recommend. $10-$20 will fill you up for hours.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "6 months ago", "authorName": "Jay J"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "My friend says "you gotta try this place, it's in Plano". I'm thinking maybe not since he's had a few misses. He catches me one day for lunch and take the offer to try The Latin Pig. We pull up and from the outside I can see it's not a big place. This is starting to get exciting.

We walk in and I like the look and feel of the place. I'm now starting to regret not coming here last time he offered. I watch as the staff brings out plates to other guests and I'm super impressed. I'm starting to have menu anxiety.

Menu anxiety: when you see so much yummy stuff, you don't know what to order from the menu.

The waiter is pretty fast on taking our drink orders and gets the back pretty fast. I'm so busy watching the food the other customers are eating that I didn't even look at the menu. My buddy Dan orders a Cubano sandwich and orders it Floridian style. Rather than deal with my menu anxiety, I order the same. He suggests we split a fry, I reluctantly agreed since I love fries and hate to share.

The food is out pretty fast and sat in front of us with fries. I realize now it was a good decision to split a fry.

WOW WOW WOW WOW WOW WOW!! This food looks good!!

I take my first bite. WOW WOW WOW WOW WOW WOW!! This is not a sandwich, this is a SAMMICH!!! and a good SAMMICH at that!! LOL

I'm eating my food contemplating my next visit and what I will order.

So to break it down for you. The place looks also, it has a very Cuban feel to it. I've never been to cuba, but I've seen movies and have a good imagination.

The service is A+, the feel is A+ and the food in incredible.

It is their promise to consistently deliver quality dishes and awesome customer service, while dining in authentic Havana 1950's d√©cor, and they deliver 100%. Bravo Latin Pig, I'm a new regular customer!", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "3 weeks ago", "authorName": "Desmond Smith"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "I had the pleasure of dining at this Cuban restaurant, and I must say, the experience was truly unforgettable. The food was absolutely delicious - every bite brought back warm memories of home. From the perfectly seasoned dishes to the authentic flavors, it felt like being back in Cuba, sharing a meal with family.

What made it even more special was the service. The staff was incredibly kind and attentive, treating us not just as customers but like old friends. Their warmth and hospitality made the whole experience even more meaningful.

If you're looking for a place that serves amazing Cuban food and makes you feel at home, this is it. Highly recommended!", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "3 months ago", "authorName": "Carlos"}]

reviews:
[{"rating": 5, "text": "The food was amazing. You can taste the authenticity. The dishes came out with so much flavor. We tried several dishes that included lamb, Yak and some vegan options. I appreciated that they offered several dishes for vegans so everyone had options. The staff are so friendly and ready to help. I will return and return until I've tried the entire menu.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "2 months ago", "authorName": "Ray"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "I wish I could give more than 5 stars!
This hidden gem in a small town truly impressed me with its incredible Himalayan and Indian fusion cuisine. The food is not only beautifully presented but also packed with authentic flavors. Everything is freshly made, and you can really taste the quality in each bite.
Karma and Khem helped us during our time here and were friendly.

The service was excellent, and the portion sizes are generous‚Äîall at a very affordable price. I visited on a Monday evening, and the place was jam-packed, which speaks volumes about its popularity.

Highly recommend trying the Spinach Chaat‚Äîrefreshing and full of flavor. The Fried Paneer Chilli Momos were absolutely outstanding, paired perfectly with a flavorful sauce. The Veg Thukpa was rich and hearty‚Äîbe sure to choose your spice level carefully; the medium was quite hot! And don‚Äôt miss the Himalayan Chai‚Äîthe cardamom notes were simply delightful.

Overall, a fantastic experience. If you enjoy bold flavors and comforting spices, this place is a must-visit!", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "4 months ago", "authorName": "Sushmitha Diwakar"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "This was my first time trying Nepali cuisine. 2 different servers offered great help and advice on popular dishes. I ordered Traditional Napali Momo, Chicken Bhuna, and Garlic Naan. All 3 were delicious and very large portions. If I lived in the area I would come back often and try more of the menu. Delicious and highly recommended.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "3 months ago", "authorName": "Samuel Puckhaber"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "Staff is so nice and helpful when recommending dishes! reviews: [{"rating": 5, "text": "This place was phenomenal! The service was excellent‚Äî the staff was so friendly and even brought us free chai to try (which is amazing there, by the way). reviews:
[{"rating": 5, "text": "This truly is Christiansburg‚Äôs hidden gem. The service is wonderful, the food is amazing, and the building itself is so clean and beautiful. The nice lady who served us was very nice and was quick to tend to our needs. Also, they had plush seating and clean tables, and she was more than welcome to bring together our table for a larger party. They have 2 single restrooms, and they were very clean and sleek. I was surprised to see this quality, so they obviously care about service. They even have a sign that says ‚ÄúPlease let us know if the restroom needs attention‚Äù which shows their care. The food was delicious and fast for the large quantity. They also had local artwork on display available for purchase. The whole experience was great, definitely stop by here. The moment we walked in, we were greeted by a polite lady with a warm smile. She explained their menu and what their best sellers are. Something we haven‚Äôt had done in other places we have eaten at. We placed the kids order which were Mac and cheese, fries and chicken nuggets. We ordered a Philly steak with fries and the Appalachian Smash burger with pasta salad with homemade lemonade.

Our food was brought out shortly after. The food was simply amazing. The prime rib for the Philly sub was cooked to perfection. The burgers on the Appalachian Smash was seasoned and cooked perfectly along with a jam and pimento cheese. The pasta salad was the best I‚Äôve had in quite a long time. The Mac and cheese and nuggets were good as well.

I love my lemonade and I‚Äôve had some horrible lemonade at some places but let me tell you, their lemonade is out of this world. It had to be the best lemonade I have ever drank. reviews:
[{"rating": 5, "text": "I felt like I was back in Montreal‚Ä¶.

reviewSummary: People say this Brazilian restaurant offers a wide variety of delicious meats, including lamb chops, and a generous selection of appetizers and side dishes. They highlight the all-you-can-eat Brazilian BBQ experience, the fun and festive atmosphere with live samba dancers, and the friendly and attentive staff. They also like the fresh cocktails and the spacious interior, perfect for special occasions.
reviews:
[{"rating": 5, "text": "If you‚Äôre looking for one of the best Brazilian steakhouses in LA, Kravings is the place to go.
It‚Äôs a Brazilian fusion restaurant, combining Brazilian churrasco, Middle Eastern kabobs, and Asian-style BBQ meats. All of these are included in the $72.99 all-you-can-eat menu, along with a variety of side dishes and a generous selection of hot and cold Brazilian foods.
There‚Äôs no buffet station ‚Äî everything is brought out fresh from the kitchen.
We loved every bite!", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "6 months ago", "authorName": "Michael Chahin"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "The Brazilian BBQ experience here is next level ‚Äì endless tableside meat served straight from the skewer. My favorite was definitely the lamb chops ‚Äì so tender and flavorful!

The unlimited apps and sides were a great balance to all the meats. Loved the berry salad, roasted beets, and that cheesy bread is a must!

The staff was super friendly and made us feel right at home. Plus, the live samba dancer was so fun and interactive!", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "5 months ago", "authorName": "Pinhwa Su"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "I went there for dinner for the first time, and so did my friends. We were all impressed. There were a lot of food options in the all-you-can-eat Brazilian BBQ course. The meats were very tender and delicious. The variety of fresh salads was also tasty. There was more food than we could eat. I definitely recommend this restaurant to my other friends!", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "6 months ago", "authorName": "Mayumi I."}, {"rating": 5, "text": "Sizzling Meats + Endless Sides = Brazilian BBQ Feast to remember!!

I love the gorgeous decor! Makes for a wonderful ambiance.

It‚Äôs an All-You-Can-Eat dining experience with fire roasted beef, chicken, pork, seafood and pineapple over an open flame! Appetizers and Side dishes are included!

They have a full bar with Handcrafted Cocktails & Wine. Live Samba Shows on Wed-Sat 7:30-8:30pm. There‚Äôs a Private Room that can hold up to 90 Guests.

Brunch (Saturday & Sunday) $52.99 + 18% service charge and tax
Dinner $72.99 + 18% service charge and tax", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "6 months ago", "authorName": "Michele Leocadio"}, {"rating": 1, "text": "I‚Äôll start off be saying my family has hosted events here for years and we have always had a great experience- especially with Louis, one of the managers. However, this last event that we held at Kravings was just okay and the treatment we received from manager David afterwards means we will not be coming back again.

We held my son‚Äôs baptism brunch here, and Louis with the manager in charge that day. When we came in he immediately recognized my family and was incredibly generous with his hosting. My guests enjoyed the food but we had several food items missing, particularly the lox from the brunch menu. This was disappointing because I have a few guests who only eat fish. Not to mention the steak, kabob etc was never brought out.

I had 4 guests who came later than expected and they were not given the full service (several dishes not brought out, not offered drinks etc). It was like they wanted us to just leave, even thought our contract allowed us to have the room until 3pm.

I worked with David- the other manager- on the contract, and initially he was great to work with. When I emailed him after the even stating we didn‚Äôt receive several items and that we had a guest who did not eat and should not be charged and wanted a partial refund, he became defensive and rude over email, stating he needed to ‚Äúclarify‚Äù things for me that occurred, even though that had nothing to do with the missing items or being charged for one extra person or having 4 guests not get the full service.

There were a few other things that did not go well on this day, but the experience was still good for my guests overall. I am mostly appalled at this level of engagement with David. What used to be a place that held fond memories for my family, and was supposed to be a happy day for my firstborn child is now bitter because of the treatment we received.

My family and I will not be returning and I recommend you just go to Fogo de Chao for your event- it will cost the same and the food will be better.

EDIT TO RESPOND TO OWNER: David, I don‚Äôt understand why you continue to make false claims about the event and what you assume you provided. You were contractually obligated to provide ALL the food you offered on the menu which we discussed on the phone and via text, and your team simply did not provide it. It should not be based on demand, I had instructed it to come out well before the event. If this were any other restaurant and we paid for something from the menu and did not receive it, we would not be charged for it. Simple as that. Additionally, I did not ask for any sort of accommodation except that you refunded the money for the four guests that did not receive the full service, and they themselves felt rushed and dissatisfied. You can try to be diplomatic on a public forum like google but your email responses to me were rude and disrespectful and tried to manipulate the facts of event when you were not even present. It was truly your email exchanges with me that colored this experience, nothing else. Again, my family and I will go elsewhere for our banquet needs in the future.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "in the last week", "authorName": "Angie G"}]

reviewSummary:
People say this fried chicken takeaway offers delicious chicken, sides, and sauces, with the Nashville medium heat level being a popular choice. They also highlight the generous portions, crispy chicken, and the croissant beignets.

Other reviews mention the prices can be high.
reviews:
[{"rating": 3, "text": "I had a real craving for Chicken Tenders and decided to give Cluck a try after reading the reviews.

I tried 3-tenders (al a cart, as you can't get different flavors otherwise) and while the tenders were good, I was a bit disappointed in the price. After the order of 3 tenders and 1 sauce (not included), the price came out to $18. That seems exorbitant for something that wasn't even a meal, but to get more than one flavor of tender, you can't order their meal...

The tenders themselves were good, fresh and crunchy, albeit a bit greasier than I would've hoped. I went through handfulls of napkins, even when using a knife and fork. I also wished the tenders had a crunchier exterior. The interior was juicy and tender, however.

The sauce (a chipotle mayo, I believe) was tasty, but nothing spectacular.

All in all, I likely won't go back, but if I were to offer encouragement to their management, it would be to let people pick their flavors regardless of meal or order. I understand not doing 1 wing per sauce, but a large tender seems like you might be able to make that work.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a week ago", "authorName": "K.C. Hohensee"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "Amazing place for some not so ordinary chicken and sides. I must say the sauces are hands down some of the best around with the taste of natural ingredients. The Nashville medium was just right like little red riding hood picking what suits her. Do not forget about the Mac, bomb.com, yes I said it!
Thank you to the staff for the amazing food and great customer service.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "3 months ago", "authorName": "M S"}, {"rating": 4, "text": "I want to preface this review by saying the service is still great. Staff is always friendly and helpful when deciding.

Over the past two years they've gone more "corporate" which means stuff isn't the same as is used to be. The tenders are still large and juicy and now they have a broader range of sauces but the original ones aren't the same. They've toned them all down so where I used to go with medium, now I have to go with hot to get the same kick. The problem is the habanero flavor on the hot is reduced so again, not the same as it used to be. It's also missing the honey drizzle that seals the deal on the lower level flavors.

Prices also changed to accommodate the full meal which is ok priced as a combo but means chicken alone is more expensive.

The Mac and cheese which used to be amazing now tastes worse than what's served at a cheap buffet.

At least the waffle fries are still good.

We miss the old boxes with the chicken cutouts.

Like I said I it feels like it's made changes at the recommendation of an outside "corporate" advisor. If you start seeing more franchises pop up, then it makes sense. Just stinks to compare the amazing past versions and the modern mass market versions.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a week ago", "authorName": "K Duon"}, {"rating": 3, "text": "Found a new Nashville Hot Chicken spot in Redlands today, Cluck Kitchen. @cluckkitchen

They had a variety of dry rubs, heat levels, and sauces for everyone. Upon the cashiers recommendation, I went with the medium heat level. I was torn between medium and hot and was advised that the hot is HOT. I'm grateful she steered me towards the medium because it was just enough heat to be enjoyable. While I could have eaten the hot, I would have been crying the whole time.

The food is cooked to order, which means that it takes just a little bit longer. The extra few minutes are total worth it, though. The chicken comes out still steaming with every bite.

My only beef is that on a 2 tender combo, I wasn't able to try two different heat levels. Both tenders had to be the same. I would have liked to have the opportunity to try one medium and one hot.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "8 months ago", "authorName": "Aimee Wilkins"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "Wow!!!
