I like extreme heat and this was testing my upper limits. Now my nephew got the four nuggets at regular flavor and those tasting AMAZING. The waffle fries were perfectly toasted on the outside and soft on the inside. Oh and the hush puppies were had a light coating and when you bite into them it‚Äôs like biting into a soft corn muffin. The staff was super friendly and was tentative to see if we needed anything else. I truly Love the service, the place is spotless and the food was made to order so we only waited 10-12 minutes. I highly recommend this place to everyone! For first timers‚Ä¶don‚Äôt go full heat unless you‚Äôre use to eating the last dab, or the bomb hot sauce as a comparative heat level. generativeSummary: Relaxed all-you-can-eat eatery serving vegan Vietnamese-inspired fare along with noodles and sandwiches.

generativeSummary: Casual, vegan eatery known for pasta dishes, burgers, sandwiches and cocktails, plus a monster theme.
editorialSummary: Venture dispensing vegan comfort food & cocktails in a chill locale with neon lights.
reviewSummary: People say this vegan restaurant serves delicious pasta, mac and cheese balls, fries, and cheesesteaks. They highlight the fun, unique, and themed atmosphere, and the creative mocktails. They also like the friendly and attentive service.
reviews:
[{"rating": 5, "text": "THIS PLACE IS MAGIC!!!! I legit want to leave more than 5 stars for this place!! üéÉüëªüîÆ

We LOVED Monster Vegan. The decor, the vibe, the staff, the FOOD. How cool and unique is this place? A HORROR/HALLOWEEN themed bar/restaurant? YES PLEASE!

Fully vegan menu. Tons of comfort vegan food choices.

We got the vegan smash burger & cheesesteak - both amazing. The vegan smash burger was massive- loaded with cheese & sauce & just magic. We also got some of the appetizers- vegan Mac bites were to die for. The waiter was super friendly. Food came out pretty quick - hot and fresh. Fried Oreos & ice cream for dessert- yes please!

We loved the entire vibe. The uplighting inside added to the charm. We really enjoyed chilling inside with all the cool spooky decor, eating delicious food with horror movies playing on the wall.

Literally such a unique place! Alllll the Halloween & quirk vibes serving up amazing vegan food! Make a reservation & dine in one of the cities most unique spots!", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "3 weeks ago", "authorName": "Heather Boswick"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "Cool concept and atmosphere. The staff were helpful, and friendly. You can tell that they actually like what they do. My food came out fast, and it was delicious. I would go back for sure.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "3 weeks ago", "authorName": "Jeremy Collins Sr."}, {"rating": 5, "text": "I had been hearing good things about this place and finally got around to going. I‚Äôm vegan, my friend isn‚Äôt but was willing to try it with me. It‚Äôs a really cute theme restaurant with drinks to match. I had the Blobarita and my friend had the Manhattan. Both drinks came out festive, the Blobarita in a monster glass and the manhattan had smoke coming from it.

For appetizers we had the fried eggplant caprese and the carne asada tacos. They were both tasty. I really enjoyed the ricotta in the eggplant caprese. For entrees I had the clams and linguine (with gluten free pasta) and my friend had the spicy bolognese. The portion sizes were large and both of us got to go containers. The clams and linguine were ok the first night, but when I ate the leftovers the next night it was delicious as all the flavors had come together. My friend liked his dish. I tried the italian sausage and sauce and they were good. I gave the food 4 stars since the pasta was just ok the first night.

They charge an automatic 20% gratuity, but it‚Äôs in big bold red letters on the bottom of the menu so there is no surprise. The service, food and atmosphere were great so we had no issues. We will definitely be back.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "5 months ago", "authorName": "Reyna L."}, {"rating": 5, "text": "What a fun, spooky spot for Vegan diners! Staff were super friendly, and they even had a little problem with the internet for the first half of my visit so there was no music or video playing, and they all kept apologizing for the inconvenience. I didn‚Äôt mind though because the restaurant was decked out in spookiness with masks on the wall and more. The food was BOMB. My favourite was the Fried Mac and Cheese Balls. How often do we see these on menus but can‚Äôt order because they are not vegan! So it was a TREAT to be able to enjoy the hot commodity that they are. When the internet came back on, they had Halloween classic tunes playing and old horror movies playing on the projector. And this place was BUSY. Would definitely recommend for a vegan restaurant that is FUN.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "2 weeks ago", "authorName": "Hailey Lewis"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "so beyond amazing. i really enjoyed my time here and all of the food and drinks we tried were very tasty. the theme is so cool and aesthetically pleasing plus the good service makes this a 10/10 for me. one of my favorite vegan restaurants in the area.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a week ago", "authorName": "priscila vega"}]

[{"rating": 1, "text": "This is the last time we will order from this place. We order the same thing, EVERY TIME! And there is ALWAYS something wrong! We always order the pecan chicken salad with mixed greens. This time there‚Äôs no pecans whatsoever on this salad and there‚Äôs enough walnut pieces that I can count them on two hands.
This is not mixed greens. This is iceberg lettuce with a couple of pieces of other greens in it.
As you can see, the tomatoes are rotten and even have mold on them.
The bread tastes like it was made an hour ago and re-toasted. What kind of restaurant are you running over there? We live super close and the salad used to be on point and so good, seriously have been ordering them for the past year. It‚Äôs all we eat from this place. After numerous complaints to them where they give you a 10% discount off of a $15 bullshit salad.
Today we paid over $30 for two salads and as you can see by the pictures, not worth it at all with moldy tomatoes, no pecans And no mixed green straight up iceberg. This place is a rip off and I don‚Äôt know who‚Äôs running it now but you need to go back to the old managers or whoever‚Äôs in charge of the kitchen because it absolutely sucks!
Even the chicken is not the same, they‚Äôre putting 6 to 7 strips when they used to put 10 to 12 pretty large very well-made strips of chicken.
For a place in Hopewell, this is Absolutely by far the worst place in our little Township , terrible! Do not eat here . If you can‚Äôt even make a salad right without putting fresh food in it and doing what the customer requests, Do not waste your time and money!", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "9 months ago", "authorName": "sabrina simpkins"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "Food was amazing! We came to celebrate a birthday and brought our dessert. It was very cool and humid, and the floors were a little slick. Our server, Jerek, was absolutely amazing and after we sat down immediately brought out drinks and bread with oil. I got the Manhattan clam chowder as an appetizer and a great flavor. Another person in our party got a stuffed pepper soup and it was very good.
For dinner I had the chicken Parm petite meal and the petite meal itself was big! Our party also got pesto tortellini, which was fantastic and a chicken avocado meal, which was all right, but the sauce was not what was described. Looked to my left and saw something on the salt that upon zooming in with a photo looked like a bug. After letting the server know, they came back showed me it was actually a price of metal from the salt shaker top. Cool not eating bugs but eating metal is better I guess. Server was very nice though. Onto the nachos... They put chili sauce instead of salsa on the nachos... Very strange. So chili nachos is what it should actually say on the menu. The salad was very humorous because it looked fantastic when it was put on the table, until you got underneath the "show lettuce" I'll call it. Once you got past the fresh salad underneath was wilting and old greens. Old trick but still in fashion!
I got a turkey club and my guest got a chicken breast meal with fries on the side. Fries never came, and my guest is presently firmly affixed to the toilet.
The walls were dirty and the booths were ripped. In my guests' booth she had a board coming up into the middle of the seat cushion. She had to sit to one side of it or the other.

Final Thoughts: Very little care by the management/owners here is the only conclusion I can come up with. The store looks amazing from the outside, but the inside... Not so much. When the dining room looks like this you can imagine what the kitchen looks like. I would say only eat here if you were given a gift card like I was. The only saving grace was the server. generativeSummary: Kebab, bolani, and other Afghan comfort food in a casual space with Afghan decor.
editorialSummary: Corner spot offering kebabs & other Afghan classics in an earth-toned, stone-walled space.
reviewSummary:
People say this Afghan restaurant serves delicious, juicy kebabs and flavorful bolani. They also highlight the generous portions of rice and the authentic, charming atmosphere with Afghan music.

Other reviews mention the service can be slow.
reviews:
[{"rating": 2, "text": "Disappointed with the takeout experience.
I had previously dined at this restaurant and had a great experience‚Äîdelicious food and generous, unlimited sauces, which really elevated the meal. That made me excited to order takeout this time. Unfortunately, the experience didn‚Äôt match up.

Each dish cost around $22, but they only included one small sauce per container. When I asked for more, I was charged an additional ~$3 for extra sauces, most of which I didn‚Äôt end up liking. It felt stingy compared to the in-restaurant experience, and it definitely took away from the overall enjoyment.

Sad to say, I was really disappointed this time. I hope they consider treating takeout customers with the same quality and generosity as dine-in.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "3 months ago", "authorName": "Frank Blue"}, {"rating": 4, "text": "Went for a combination of Kabob. We only come here for special occasion since it's expensive. You will want to try verity and take the left over home. Yummy.

I highly recommend this if you like Afghan food. If you have not try, you should. Order what I ordered for 4.

Bolani
Combination: Murgh & Teka (Chicken & Beef)
Triple Kabob: Murgh, Teka & Chaplee Kabob
Mantu (Dumplings)
Quabili Pallow

May be I should go to dinner there tonight. :-)", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "7 months ago", "authorName": "Prat Prathnadi"}, {"rating": 4, "text": "Big ups to this place for cooking delicious kebab that's perfectly juicy (succulent, even).

reviewSummary: People say this restaurant serves delicious fried green tomato BLTs, waffles, and breakfast sandwiches. They highlight the good value for the price and the unique, fresh flavors. They also like the friendly staff and quick service.
reviews:
[{"rating": 5, "text": "Wow! Wowowow! Such delicious food. Everything on the menu looked phenomenal. I got the fried green tomato BLT and a cinnamon roll (who can pick just 1 thing?!) and wish I could eat here for every meal for the next 6 months", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "in the last week", "authorName": "Rachel Moenart"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "I would give 10 stars if I could.  5 adults on vacation and we ate at a LOT of restaurants in the area:  Jack's Shop Kitchen is the best.  I'm not kidding; and some of the other spots I wholeheartedly gave 5 star reviews.

Great food.  Seriously, each one of us ordered something different from their menu, and every meal was delicious.  I can confidently recommend everything.

Prices, staff, ambiance, decor, service, cleanliness -- all great.  Menu items were unique, while still delivering all the tasty familiar comfort cuisine.  If you are anywhere in the area . . .  anywhere in western Virginia, I suggest eating here.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "5 months ago", "authorName": "Clete S'on"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "Consistently delicious!  Breakfast, lunch, or dinner it‚Äôs all good! Great service!  We love the variety and flavor combinations made fresh to order.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "2 months ago", "authorName": "R Rod"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "We have found our new favorite restaurant!!! (I‚Äôm not kidding.. we will be bringing any celebration, family visiting, or just casual Tuesday night to Jacks Shop.

This was one of the best meals we‚Äôve had since we moved to Charlottesville a year ago.

We got the their Smoked Trout Spread‚Ä¶ this was one of the best spreads and pita I‚Äôve had.

The mussels and fries blew me away‚Ä¶ the sauce, flavor, deliciousness‚Ä¶ SO GOOD.

For our mains we got the Roasted Chicken and Special (Shrimp and Scallop fettuccine)

This was some of the most fresh, flavorful, delightful we‚Äôve ever had..

Their pasta tasted like I was sitting in Italy. The chicken was perfectly cooked my fiance wanted to go back the next night.

The inside of the restaurant is modern, cute and has the best service!! Cylie was incredibly sweet and guided us through the menu!

This is the perfect place to stop in for an incredible meal. Not too fancy. Just the dishes you crave and love. reviews: [{"rating": 5, "text": "This is my first time trying Chili Basil and will not be my last. First of all, the restaurant is gorgeous- everything is so well decorated and clean and gives off a very nice ambiance. There was outdoor seating but I prefer indoors- so that‚Äôs where I decided to sit. As for my food, I went for a light brunch so I got a Thai tea- which was delicious. I feel like when you come to a Thai restaurant you have to try their thai tea. It wasn‚Äôt too sweet and it was creamy. As for the food, I got the pork rib and then veggie wraps with tofu and shrimp. The pork rib is nicely seasoned, not spicy, very tender‚Äî it literally fell off the bone. You get quite a lot too- so definitely can be like a sharing plate with a friend. For the wraps, the two sauces that come with it are SO GOOD. you get the crunch from the lettuce and the herbs, and you get the noodles, and then the sauce just makes everything come together. I wanna say it‚Äôs a clean bite- it‚Äôs refreshing and light and the pieces of tofu and shrimp made it very filling. -chicken tikka masala curry bowl: Finally a place the loves up to their spice level. We asked for level hot and it was legit hot! Very flavorful with lots of spice. Came with Paratha which is similar to naan but thinner and made with a mix of white and brown flour.

reviewSummary:

reviews:
[{"rating": 5, "text": "Came to Akbar as a tourist from out of state on recommendation from a friend. Let‚Äôs just say I found a great reason to return to the  Baltimore area. Authentic Indian food and experience, I will be stopping by anytime I am back in the area and you should too!

Jazz, the owner, was an incredible host and gave us great recommendations for each course of the dinner which played a huge role in getting the authentic northern Indian experience.

The restaurant was beautifully decorated and had a nice ambiance for a pleasant dining experience.

The food for every course was delicious. The appetizer sampler and lentil soup to start with a chai were perfect for a cloudy evening. We shared three delicious curry dishes paneer kofta, lamb xacutti, and lamb pasanda. The lamb was tender and cooked to perfection. All the sauces were full and flavorful. Your tastebuds will thank you.

Dessert we had the mango lassi and ice cream. I didn‚Äôt think I could fit anymore food at this point but they were both so creamy and flavorful. Do yourself a favor and don‚Äôt skip this part!

Still not convinced? Take a shot and try it out. Bring a friend and they probably won‚Äôt stop talking about it!", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "2 weeks ago", "authorName": "Jonathan Madera"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "This Indian establishment is a
one-of-a-kind special place in Baltimore. Charming! I was so excited to have discovered Akbar while passing by this morning to go to the little quick-mart a few doors down.

I ate a small breakfast, drove out to the Patapsco Valley State Park for the day, got lost in the forest and crossed a part in the river that soaked my socks and shoes, only to climb up the side of the park hill to get back onto the trail, made it to the Jeep, followed through with going to Manor Hill Tavern in Ellicott City to have a beer BUT I had stayed extremely disciplined to not eat a single thing there even though I was so hungry because I knew what I was saving myself for and that was Akbar!

So here‚Äôs a shout out to Akbar and their staff and all the hard work that is paying off for them. Well done you guys. Outstanding team! Outstanding aesthetics! Outstanding atmosphere! Outstanding ambience!
And most of all outstanding food!

If this is your first time having Indian food, always start off with Chicken Madras around a level 3, like the perfect spiciness -not too basic; not too spicy. And lastly: Dear Akbar, I will be sending my love to you all all the way back from down in hot, steamy Florida and I will shout it loud that I am thankful you Akbar exist. Thank you for being here and gifting new customers and returning customers with your grace. Keep up the great work! If I sound corny and ridiculous I do apologize lol. But I am giving a genuine, wholehearted compliment.

Love, Kourtney", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "3 weeks ago", "authorName": "Kourtney"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "This quiet and authentic Indian restaurant features great decorative designed and service. This is a great place to dine as a family. They serve a buffet and dishes. Would recommend to vegetarians and vegans. The owner was our waiter and was very polite and respectful. I loved the atmosphere. The food was Exquisite and flavorful as there was just the right amount of everything.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "7 months ago", "authorName": "Shaany Raut"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "Akbar is one of my favorite neighborhood restaurants. I live right around the corner and have gotten both takeout and dined in. Every time I go, the staff is very friendly and the food is always excellent. The naan in particular is better than most Indian restaurants in Baltimore. Fluffy, not too chewy, great flavor. My only complaint is sometimes it‚Äôs pretty empty inside- but that‚Äôs not even the restaurant‚Äôs fault. People order takeout way more often and dine-in less than they used to compared to pre-2020.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "2 weeks ago", "authorName": "Laura Hinson"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "Fantastic place. The lunch buffet had many options for meat eaters and vegetarians and they made the naan to order. Highly recommend and you can‚Äôt beat it at $15", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "4 months ago", "authorName": "Rachel Murphy"}]

reviews: [{"rating": 5, "text": "This Raman bar is incredible. Amazing staff great environment. The Ramen is the best anywhere! The best I ever had. reviewSummary: People say this Peruvian restaurant serves delicious lomo saltado, ceviche, and tallar√≠n. They highlight the tender meat, flavorful dishes, and generous portions. They also like the friendly staff and welcoming atmosphere.
reviews:
[{"rating": 5, "text": "It‚Äôs been a while since we had good Peruvian food . One of our chef friends recommended Picante to us. They open at 10:30am. We didn‚Äôt have breakfast so we were pretty hungry by the time we arrived at 11am.  The interior is simple and quaint with cool murals on the wall when you enter. We shared the Anticuchos de corazon to start. It was my first time having it but with the way the season and grill it, I just thought it was steak . We both got our ‚Äúgo to‚Äù Peruvian dishes; Lomo Saltado for me and Tallarin Verde con Lomo for my husband . We ate every last bit of our food, so delicious. Service was also super friendly. They‚Äôre going to be opening a second location featuring Peruvian chicken in Upland so we‚Äôre super excited for that. Can‚Äôt wait‚Ä¶ üòù", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "2 months ago", "authorName": "Charlene C"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "Hidden gem! I came here because a Peruvian friend recommended it and I seriously fell in love. The food is so good, the meat in the lomo is super tender and full of flavor, the tallar√≠n was delicious, and my favorite has to be the ceviche! I‚Äôm used to Mexican-style ceviche so this was a bit different for me, but I loved it. On top of the food, the service is always great! the staff is really nice and even though the place is small, they do their best to fit bigger groups. Definitely recommend trying this spot!", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a month ago", "authorName": "Ruby Garcia"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "Small but bright restaurant with great Peruvian flavors. We really enjoyed the loco saltado.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a month ago", "authorName": "Michael Ong"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "Best Lomo a la huancaina I‚Äôve ever tried in Los Angeles. The service was great, it was only one server for all the tables and she nailed it. The food was delicious and the maracuya ü§§", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "6 months ago", "authorName": "Nat Solis"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "As a proud Peruvian, I was excited to hear from family that a new Peruvian restaurant had opened nearby‚Äîand I had to try it for myself. I placed a takeout order around 7:45 PM on a Sunday, and despite arriving close to closing time, the staff welcomed me warmly with a fresh, hot meal ready to go.

The restaurant was in the process of closing and cleaning for the next day‚Äîmopping and sanitizing‚Äîbut still had a lively, welcoming atmosphere, with customers happily finishing their meals. As a business owner myself, I really appreciated their professionalism and cleanliness.

Now, onto the food‚Äîmy lomo saltado was absolutely incredible. Perfectly seasoned, tender meat, fluffy rice, and just the right balance of spices. To top it off, they even had Diet Inka Kola for those of us who need our fix!

This place is a gem, and I‚Äôll definitely be supporting this small business again. 10/10!", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a month ago", "authorName": "Leia Sosa"}]

reviews:
[{"rating": 5, "text": "Great experience at Spice Wing. 1st time. Wings were hot and fresh crispy with just the right amount of seasoning. Staff were great snd place was so clean. Very impressed.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a month ago", "authorName": "Travel_with_tripp"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "Chezzi wings w all seasonings on the fries is the best combo you can get. They are very hospitable inside, and very accommodating. Best wings I have ever had", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a month ago", "authorName": "Bryce Fowler"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "The food was cooked fresh, the tenders are HUGE, you definitely get what you pay for. Everyone was kind and made sure we were satisfied with our food.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "4 weeks ago", "authorName": "Cecilia Garza"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "Skeptical at first.  Seemed expensive fo some chicken tenders. It was amazing.
The portions are massive.  The chicken is soft and fresh. The sides were fresh and delicious.  I think this might have become our new favorite chicken place.
Thank you!!", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a week ago", "authorName": "Melinda Demlow"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "If you‚Äôre a fan of chicken wings, you owe it to yourself to visit Spice Wing in Newnan. This gem of a restaurant not only serves up some great wings but also offers a level of customer service that truly sets it apart.
From the moment you walk in, you‚Äôre greeted with a warm welcome that makes you feel right at home. The staff go above and beyond to ensure your dining experience is nothing short of fantastic. Their genuine friendliness and attentiveness are evident throughout your visit‚Äîwhether you‚Äôre asking for recommendations or need a quick refill, they‚Äôre on top of it with a smile.

Now, let‚Äôs talk about the wings. Spice Wing offers an impressive variety of flavors, each one crafted with care and creativity. Whether you‚Äôre craving the classic buffalo heat, a sweet and smoky barbecue, or something more adventurous like a zesty lemon pepper, each wing is perfectly cooked‚Äîcrispy on the outside, tender on the inside, and generously coated in delicious sauce and spice. We opted for the ‚Äúchezzi‚Äù spice which is a combination of their top seasonings and sauce and it was amazing.
But the excellence doesn‚Äôt stop there. The attention to detail extends to every aspect of the meal. The side dishes are just as noteworthy, with 4 different types of crispy fries, with some great seasoning options. The variety of sides continues with some amazing jalape√±o poppers and many other things that we will have to try on our next visit.
The waffles and fried Oreos were imaculate as well.

What really stands out is how the staff manages to make each visit feel special. Their knowledge of the menu and enthusiasm for the food make it clear that they‚Äôre passionate about what they do. They‚Äôre attentive without being intrusive, and their personalized service enhances the overall dining experience. I entire visit lasted about an hour and I noticed the staff were quick to greet the regular customers by their first name, which really stands out to me.
In a world where good food and great service always go hand in hand, these guys excel on both fronts. It‚Äôs a place where you can count on delicious wings and exceptional customer care every single time.
Highly recommended for anyone who loves great food and appreciates top-notch service!", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "a year ago", "authorName": "Asad Panjwani"}]

reviewSummary: Diners say this chicken wings restaurant serves up delicious Dirty Elvis wings, Cambodian Dirt wings, and garlic noodles. They also highlight the friendly and helpful staff, and the quick service.
reviews:
[{"rating": 5, "text": "Ordered the jalape√±o wings and spicy elephant  wings with small garlic noodles.
Chicken was juicy fresh and crispy on the outside and the garlic noodles were tasty with a tangy hint at the end of your bite.
The jalape√±os wings and garlic noodles were a perfect combination.  The spicy elephant was full of peanut flavor and a perfect texture to the sauce, not spicy but not sweet just full of flavor.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "4 months ago", "authorName": "Lloyd Domingo"}, {"rating": 4, "text": "Friendly. Fast service. Clean.
The Cambodian Dirt did not have any lemograss taste to it--boo.
Dirty Elvis was good, it didn't remind me of Khmer flavors though.
Maybe the Tanarind Tiger would...

A bit far for me and I normally don't eat fried wings or noodles. Even so, good taste adventure.

If you like fried wings, noodles, rice, this is a great place to load up. Add Khmai tea to the order. Bon apetit!", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "4 months ago", "authorName": "Ya- Ya"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "Hole in the wall with great wings! They're all pretty damn good and I love my wings extra saucy but surprisingly my favorites are Dirty Cambodian, Jalapeno MSG, and Pekang with a side of fries seasoned with dirty Cambodian or Pekang. No knock on the sauced ones at all! Noodles are decent and rice is just OK", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "4 months ago", "authorName": "Michael Briones"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "The wings are amazing.  Anyone who eats wings needs to try this place !!!! The taste is out of this world.
The fried rice and the garlic noodles are great !!!! I will recommend this place to everyone who wants chicken wings.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "3 months ago", "authorName": "Carlos R"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "We drive 15 miles across LA just for these wings. Is there a greater demonstration of love in Los Angeles? Idk, but what I do know is that Shlap Muan is, quite simply, the best. Pekang is our favorite, it is PERFECTION, the spices blend so beautifully with the chicken, it‚Äôs honestly a contender for my last meal choice. But we have yet to try one we don‚Äôt like, and also love the Water Buffalo and Cambodian Dirt. Dirty Elvis is great too. A lil messy, this is maybe not ‚Äúfirst-date food‚Äù, but frankly, this is the only ‚Äúmarry-me-chicken‚Äù I want. Love you, Shlap!", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "3 months ago", "authorName": "Victoria Kato"}]

generativeSummary: Casual restaurant dishing up jerk chicken and other Jamaican eats such as stew chicken, goat plates and beef patties for take-out or dine-in.
reviewSummary:
People say this Jamaican restaurant serves delicious oxtails, plantains, and cabbage with generous portions. They also highlight the authentic taste, the hearty portions, and the reasonable prices.

Other reviews mention the rice can be mushy.
reviews: [{"rating": 5, "text": "This was my first time visiting Jamaican Vibez in Fayetteville, NC. As soon as I walked in the door I was greeted by all of the employees. The young lady Beverly was kind in answering the questions that I had. She also gave me a quick run down on the type of plates I can order. She was patient and pleasant. I only ordered a side of the Oxtails this go round which Beverly did let me know that it is priced by the weight. My Oxtails were not cut in half, and they tasted fantastic! All of the hot food looked fresh and cold desserts looked fresh. They were well stocked. The cashier was very customer friendly as well and offered to put a little gravy on my Oxtails after the Oxtails were weighted so that I did not get charged for the extra weight from the gravy and I appreciate that. I will most definitely be returning to try even more of there dishes. What really topped this visit off was that I walked in and 5 minutes later I was eating my food!! Thank you ladies for the great customer service.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "2 months ago", "authorName": "Michelle McMillian"}, {"rating": 2, "text": "I drove all the way up to Fayetteville on my way out of town to get some food. I was so disappointed I ordered the combo oxtail and curry goat no veggies extra rice. The employees was very respectful BUT as a culinary professional I was disappointed with what I say employee eating behind the line music too loud. The young lady wasn't bad with service but was very stingy with the protein you can see what I paid for a WHOLE oxtail that was cut in HALF so you can CHEAT the customers The juices was delicious so was the beef patties But the main for the plate was very lacking with the two protein combination I was giving one oxtail cut in HALF as for the goat BONES. Enjoy the money for the combo plate I WILL NEVER SUPPORT THIS PLACE EVER AGAIN. I rather go to Circle K and get a Hot dog that's been sitting there for hours\n\n** Curry in Plate is mine notice the size and portion", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "4 months ago", "authorName": "DELON SOLOMON"}, {"rating": 4, "text": "Very good and authentic Jamaican cuisine. Service feels rushed so you'd better know what you want. Portions are large and worth the price. Minimal seating and small area, so I'd suggest takeout", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "3 months ago", "authorName": "Cas"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "Come and enjoy some authentic Jamaican  food. This place is clean, very good customer service. The food is very flavorful. Rice and peas with brown stew chicken, cabbage, fried plantains. I also brought a beef patty.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "5 months ago", "authorName": "Georgia"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "Best damn lunch I‚Äôve had while being here. Friendly staff, food was always being restocked (went for their lunch buffet) and nothing came out bad. Recommend üíØ", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "2 months ago", "authorName": "Jesse White"}]

generativeSummary: Rustic eatery serving artisan pies and craft beers with a friendly atmosphere.
reviewSummary: People say this restaurant serves great pizza and has a good selection of craft beers. They highlight the fun atmosphere and the friendly, attentive staff. They also like the fresh ingredients and the option for kids to make their own pizza.
reviews:
[{"rating": 5, "text": "20251024 - Family of three

Order:
App: Twisted Skillet Garlic Butter Cheese Bombs
Salad: Caeser Salad
Pizza 1: Build your own with white sauce, meatballs, and chopped tomatoes.
Pizza 2: Deviant Sister

Ambiance: The building is awesome! Everything is super clean. The decorations are great! The pizza oven and kitchen area was out in the open and we enjoyed watching how the sausage is made so to  speak. Bathrooms are super clean!

Service: The service was top notch! Junior was our waiter and he was great! He was quick, courteous, helpful, and very kind! From one server/bartender to another, Junior did great! He's a perfect representation of the establishment.

Food: Wow!! Just wow!! The garlic cheese bombs came out screaming hot and wonderful! If you like a good cheese pull, you will love these! The salad was fresh and wonderful. The pizza crust was excellent! Crunchy however not burnt with great taste! The sauce, the veggies/meat, the cheese....not notch ingredients. I will be back to try more apps and the different options they have. You MUST try the root beer. It's awesome!!!", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "in the last week", "authorName": "Josh Casper"}, {"rating": 3, "text": "We stumbled upon Twisted Sisters Tap House by accident and decided to try two of their pizzas. We would definitely go back.", "relativePublishTimeDescription": "in the last week", "authorName": "Brandi Morrison"}, {"rating": 5, "text": "Quiet, relaxed atmosphere with good music piped in over the sound system.
